title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in 1/4 c. butter, for 10 minutes. Add chopped parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano leaves.
Combine 2 beaten eggs and 8 oz. mozzarella cheese (in another bowl).

title: spanish sauce
directions: Saute the green pepper, celery and onion in butter until soft. Add tomatoes; let simmer for 15 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Thicken mixture with flour and water thickening. Cook for 5 minutes.
Pour over omelet.

title: crab custard casserole
directions: Butter bread on both sides.
Cut into cubes.
Put first 3 ingredients into a well-greased casserole.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over crab mixture in casserole.
Cover and refrigerate all day or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve immediately.
Serves 4.
Great luncheon dish.

title: quick thai curry noodles
directions: Place cooked and drained noodles into 4 bowls.
Set aside. Heat the oil in a saucepan.
Add garlic and saute until light brown.
Add chicken and saute lightly.
Add coconut milk, red pepper, chicken broth, curry powder, turmeric, soy sauce and sugar. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Cover and turn off heat.
Let stand for 1 minute.
Add lemon juice.
Pour soup over noodles. Garnish with chopped green onions.
Serve immediately.

title: quick sangria
directions: Put ice in serving pitcher.
Fill pitcher 1/3 full with white wine.
Add orange and banana slices.
Add enough 7-Up to fill pitcher.
Add 1 to 2 ounces brandy.
Stir and serve.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Bring water to boil.
Add noodles.
Mix the cheeses and eggs together.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan. Put 3 tablespoons sauce on bottom of pan.
Spread.
Add cooked noodles.
Layer noodles, half the meat,
half the cheese mixture and half the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cover top with noodles. Cover them with sauce lightly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with pure salt (not iodized).
Cover with cracked ice.
Mix well.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain and rinse off salt brine.

title: lemon pudding(or 4 layer pudding)
directions: Whip until thick and pour on cream cheese.
Top with whipped cream, if you wish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit and nuts.
Mix Jell-O according to package. Add sugar; stir well.
Pour over fruit, then add juice and stir. Refrigerate until ready to serve with liquid.
(The juice keeps it from congealing.)

title: cinnamon apple cups
directions: Dissolve gelatin and candy in boiling water. Stir in applesauce, lemon juice and salt. Chill until partially set. Form cream cheese in tiny balls. Stir cheese balls and nuts into gelatin mixture. Spoon into small molds* and chill until firm. Serve on fruit-salad tray. Makes fifteen 1/3-cup molds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray casserole dish.
Put 4 to 6 boned chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Put 1 piece Swiss cheese on each breast.
Mix chicken soup with 1/4 to 1/2 cup wine.
Pour soup and wine mixture over chicken breasts with cheese.
Spread herb stuffing over soup.
Melt butter and pour over stuffing. Bake at 375° until chicken is done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oriental salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables.
Combine with celery, onion and green pepper in container with tight fitting lid.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, powdered sugar and butter to form a dough. Press into a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat sugar, eggs, lemon juice, 2 tablespoons of flour and baking powder.
Pour over the baked crust.
Return to oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Place in freezer for easier cutting.

title: lazy man cobbler
directions: Melt butter and put in bottom of dish. Mix sugar, flour and milk, and pour in dish. Add fruit and syrup on top. Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: nacho popcorn
directions: In a small saucepan melt the margarine.
Stir the paprika, red pepper and cumin into the melted margarine; let cool about five minutes.
Place the popcorn in large bowl.
Pour spice mixture on top; sprinkle with the cheese.
Toss with forks, coating the popcorn evenly with the spice mixture.

title: super salisbury steak
directions: Soak bread crumbs in small amount of milk.
Mix with ground beef and remaining ingredients, except cooking oil, soup and water.
Shape into patties.
Brown lightly in cooking oil.
Add soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Have butcher lard the Pot Roast.
Rub meat with pepper, nutmeg, and salt.
Place in crick or enamel pot.

title: party rye appetizer
directions: Mix equal amounts of mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread on party rye bread.
Place in broiler setting in oven until cheese is bubbly and brown.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Cook ground beef, then drain.
Add cheese, green chilies, tomatoes, Worcestershire and chili powder.
Simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Serve hot with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a large glass bowl, sift cocoa and powdered sugar together. Place margarine on top of mixture and add milk.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts and spread into an 8 x 8-inch buttered dish. Chill.

title: french cherry cream pie in a cake pan
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter; pat into a 9 x 13 pan. In a bowl, mix cream cheese and powdered sugar. In another bowl, whip whipping cream. Mix together with cream cheese mixture; pour over graham cracker crust. Smooth out and top with pie filling. Refrigerate.

title: butternut squash with cheese
directions: Cut squash in serving pieces and scoop out seeds and stringy part.
Leave rind on.
Parboil 15 minutes in salted boiling water. Drain.
Season with salt and pepper, dot with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Place chicken and vegetables in dish.
Stir together soup and broth; then pour over chicken mixture.
Combine margarine, flour and milk. Stir until smooth.
Pour over mixture in dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken and pull off the bone.
Cut into pieces.
Add vegetables and seasonings and cook all together.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Place all ingredients into a blender; blend for 1 minute. Pour mixture into 9-inch pie plate sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until custard sets.
Cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion, season to taste.
Combine enchilada sauce, soup and milk; heat.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer chips, meat and onions, sauce mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: easy pull apart buns
directions: Lightly grease muffin pan.
Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Shape into balls. Coat with mayonnaise.
Roll in sugar mixture.
Place 4 balls in each muffin cup.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy soup pot.
Add the onion and celery and cook until just soft. Whisk in the flour (use Wonder flour) and cook 3 minutes.
Slowly blend in the broth.
Bring this to a boil, reduce the heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes.
Strain and return the broth to the pot. Slowly whisk in the peanut butter and the cream.
Simmer for about 15 minutes longer.
Serve warm. Serves 4-6.

title: calamari marinara sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until soft over low flame.
Add parsley and basil.
Heat 1 minute.
Combine the rest of the ingredients, except calamad, to onion mixture and cook 1 hour. Add calamad and cook until tender, approximately 15 minutes.
Do not overcook fish.

title: melting chocolate in the microwave
directions: In a microwave bowl, place 1 square of chocolate, uncovered. Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until soft, stirring every minute. Heat 1 1/2 to 2 minutes for 1 ounce and 2 to 3 minutes for 6 ounces (1 cup).

title: ice cream wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.
Remove from pan immediately or they will stick.
Cool before servings.
(Pam or any spray shortening works great.)

title: amalene tucker's hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
(Do not beat.)
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tests done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then remove from pans and cool completely.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Add soda to 2 tablespoons boiling water and lemon juice.
Add to mashed bananas; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, then banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
This is especially moist.

title: creole seasoning
directions: Mix and use like salt.	Can be used on everything.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash sweet potatoes and add all ingredients.
Use just enough canned milk to make fluffy.
Put in baking dish.

title: coconut sour cream dream cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed and bake in two layers.
Split each layer in half.
Blend sugar, sour cream, coconut, and chill. Spread all but 1 c. of the sour cream mixture between the four layers.
Blend the remaining cup with whipped cream and spread on the top of the cake.
Seal in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
Keep refrigerated after cutting.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery until done.
Add hash browns and continue to cook.
Pour cream of celery or mushroom soup over this; stir in.
Put cheese on top of all and melt in oven for about 5 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or mushroom

title: kentucky corn bread
directions: Mix good; bake in skillet at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy oat crust
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
On nonstick baking sheet, spread oats. Bake 5 minutes or until lightly toasted, stirring once. In a bowl, combine oats with remaining ingredients.
Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Bake 10 minutes. Cool before filling. Proceed as directed in Strawberry Chiffon Pie recipe.
Makes 6 servings.

title: layered guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados with juice of lemon.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, layer mashed avocados, grated cheese, sour cream, picante sauce and chopped green onion.
Let set in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with tostadas (nacho chips).
Serves 8.

title: super summer salad
directions: Dissolve gelatins in boiling water; add marshmallows and beat with electric mixer until dissolved.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to gelatin mixture, blending all ingredients together.
Chill until firm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together.
When ready to use, use 2 to 3 tablespoons of mix and 1 cup of water.

title: butterscotch bits
directions: Melt morsels with peanut butter.
Add peanuts and broken up potato sticks.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper. These have proved to be a hit each time served.

title: spinach spread
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out moisture.
Mix other ingredients and spinach.
Chil and serve with crackers.
Make day ahead to enhance flavor.

title: hawaiian cream pie
directions: Mix flour and 2/3 cup sugar.
Add pineapple, water and lemon juice.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick and creamy.
Add beaten eggs and butter.
Cook all for 2 minutes. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue made with stiffly beaten egg whites and 3 tablespoons of sugar, browned.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Cut English muffins in half and then 1/4's and arrange on cookie sheets.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Put generous portion of mixture on each muffin piece.
Freeze for at least 30 minutes.
(Can freeze for several weeks.) When ready to use, broil for a few minutes until puffy and golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: whole wheat french bread
directions: Combine buttermilk and warm water.
The temperature of this mixture should be warm to the touch.
Sprinkle yeast over warm buttermilk mixture and let it set.
Combine flours and bran.
When yeast has dissolved and the surface is foamy, beat in 1/2 flour mixture.
Beat until dough is elastic.
Add remaining flour and salt.
Mix well.
Dough should form a ball in bowl, yet not be sticky.
Add more flour if necessary.
A stiff dough is required since loaves are baked on sheets rather than in pans and consequently have no side support.
Turn dough onto lightly floured sheets.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix soups together well and add to butter, mixing well.
Add chicken, placing down in mixture.
DO NOT SALT CHICKEN.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt.
Place in 275° oven, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Then cover and cook additional 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat with onion and green pepper.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
(You may add a little water if mixture is too thick.)

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook the chicken breasts 20 minutes. Skin and bone. Dice into small pieces.
Blend all ingredients.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch casserole with most of a large package of plain Doritos chips.
Top with chicken mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in large saucepan.
Bring to boil. Simmer three minutes.
Stir in jello and juices.
Ladle into wide topped freezer containers.
Leave 1 inch head space.
Cover tightly and freeze.

title: fresh fruit breakfast cup
directions: Combine all fruit, preparing bananas and peaches last.
No sugar or dressing is needed.
Serves 15.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Form into loaf and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Let set until it starts to jell. Whip evaporated milk.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Add Jell-O. Whip.

title: macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Lay pieces in a baking dish. Sprinkle with seasoning.
(I use garlic powder, pepper and dried basil.)
Slice onions and break into rings; cover chicken thickly with all onions.
Pour 1/2 of the barbecue sauce over onions and chicken.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour; drain excess liquid. Pour remaining sauce and bake 30 minutes more at 350°, uncovered.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup.
Add cream cheese; stir until well blended.
Add water to gelatin to dissolve.
Add to soup mixture.
Cool until slightly set.
Add mayonnaise and vegetables.
Add Worcestershire and catsup.
Add garlic powder as desired and a little black pepper.
Add shrimp and pour into greased mold.
Chill to set. Serve with crackers.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump on top of each other pineapple, then pie filling, then cake mix, then coconut, then nuts and then margarine.
Do not mix! Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Serve with sliced apples, bananas, pears, strawberries or fruit of your choice.

title: easy roast
directions: Heat oven to 250° or lower.
Salt and pepper roast. Wrap in foil. Place in shallow pan and place in oven. Go about your business for about 5 hours.

title: beef tenderloin cooked in wine
directions: Trim tenderloins and place in pan.
In order listed, add ingredients over meat.
Boil 5 to 8 minutes and turn.
Let boil 5 to 6 minutes longer. Cool and slice thin.

title: ambrosia(serves 8)
directions: Combine orange sections, coconut and sugar. Combine whipped cream and powdered sugar. Fold into fruit mixture. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, beat until fluffy.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend well and chill.
Cut out cookies, sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: recipe for friendship
directions: Mix ingredients together; toss in a little flair.
Serve to everyone you know and top with a tiny prayer.

title: beer muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat 1/2 minute.
Fill 24 nongreased medium muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix first three ingredients and cook on low heat until marshmallows dissolve.
Cool slightly then fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until becomes firm.

title: shish kabob
directions: Mix the first six ingredients together and marinate beef squares overnight.
Then place on skewer and alternate with onion, bell pepper, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cook on grill.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer each ingredient in the order listed, emptying all contents as is (pineapple, cherry pie filling, cake mix and margarine).
Top with chopped walnuts.
Use a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fettucini alfredo sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in sour cream and flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over fettucini.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and wash beans; mix.
Place alternate layers of bean mixture, onion and green pepper in salad bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix rest of ingredients for dressing; beat until white and thick.
Pour over salad and refrigerate overnight. Serves 16 to 20.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Spread on cookie sheet (greased).
Mix next 7 ingredients together.
Spread on dough.
Lay pepperoni slices all over and cover with cheese.
Roll like jelly roll. Place seam down and close ends.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot with a side dish of spaghetti sauce.

title: alligator sauce piquant
directions: *Alligator must be free of all fat; also dark meat is the best (leg and body meat), boneless.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain frozen vegetables.
Combine them with soup, 1/2 cup of cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can onions. Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.

title: fried okra
directions: Put sliced okra in large bowl. Add salt and pepper. Pour enough buttermilk to cover okra. Mix well. Put in the refrigerator about 30 minutes. Then drain buttermilk off okra. Roll in flour and drop in hot oil until brown.

title: microwave fried rice
directions: Combine onions and butter in 2 quart casserole.
Microwave on High until onions are tender, 1 to 3 minutes.
Sit aside.
Stir the bouillon in hot water until dissolved.
Add rice and green onions to casserole.
Cover.
Microwave on High until mixture boils, 4 to 8 minutes.
Let stand covered until liquid is gone, 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir in eggs and soy sauce. Microwave on High until eggs are set, 2 to 4 1/2 minutes, stirring 4 to 5 times during cooking.
Fluff with fork, then serve.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix all together.
Chill well.
(Make ice ring with additional Kool-Aid.)
Serves 60.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and place in 2-quart casserole dish.

title: banana bread
directions: Break eggs in medium mixing bowl; beat until well blended. Cut banana in 1-inch pieces into bowl with eggs.
Mash with fork and mix with eggs.
Add sugar, salad oil and nuts to banana mixture and beat until well mixed.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together into banana mixture.
Mix until dry ingredients are just blended.
Pour into greased 9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: pecan pie bar cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, butter, baking powder and brown sugar together. Mixture will be dry and crumbly. Put in bottom of well-greased 9 X 13 inch pan. Bake at 325 degrees for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spray bottoms of 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans with nonstick spray. In a large bowl, whisk together eggs and oil. Add sugar, zucchini, vanilla and molasses; mix well. Combine flours, cinnamon, salt and soda. Stir into egg mixture, mixing only until well blended. Pour into prepared pans. Bake for about 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of loaves comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely. Yield: 2 loaves (16 slices each).

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
In a separate bowl blend eggs and oil.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well. Fold in berries and nuts.
Grease 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 325` for 1 hour.
Easy!
Yields 2 loaves.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
Mix 2 teaspoons per mug of hot water.

title: cheese cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix.
In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Mix until crumbly.
Press on bottom and about halfway up sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan (or any deep pan or dish).
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Add 3 eggs and reserved cake mix.
Beat one minute on medium speed.
On low speed, gradually add milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Top with choice of pie filling.

title: chocolate chip fudge
directions: Dissolve sugar and milk well.
Add oleo and place on range. Boil for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring as it boils, until it forms a soft ball in a cup of cold water.
Add the chips and Marshmallow Creme that have been mixed in another bowl.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Add the nuts and the vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: sylvia's cake
directions: Mix ingredients on low speed until moist.
Beat 2 minutes on high.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: gelatin divinity
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water. Bring to boil. Cook until it reaches the hard-ball stage (250° to 252°).

title: 7-up salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Use juice from pineapple and water to dissolve Jell-O.
When Jell-O has started to cool, add cream cheese, pineapple and 7-Up.
Blend well in blender. Chill.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop from teaspoons into hot oil (375°).
Cook until brown.

title: pheasant stir-fry
directions: Brown pheasant pieces in a frypan with 1 tablespoon of cooking oil.
Season with 1 teaspoon garlic salt and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Add vegetables to pheasant. Pour 1/2 of the Kikkoman baste and glaze over veggies. Cover and simmer until veggies are cooked to your desired crispness.
Pour remaining glaze on servings as desired. Great on white rice.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Melt the butter in a pie plate; coat.
Beat the egg whites with the cream of tartar and the sugar.
Roll the crackers fine; add to egg whites.
Add the pecans and vanilla.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool; spread with whipped cream.
Chill 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and top with 1 stack Ritz crackers (crumbled); add melted butter if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: thirst quenching punch
directions: Yields sixty 4-ounce servings.

title: honey-ham
directions: Heat in saucepan; baste ham 1/2 way through cooking.

title: taco salad
directions: Beat all ingredients until creamy.
Spread on a plate.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped green peppers, chopped tomatoes, chopped green onion tops and grated Colby cheese.
Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Sprinkle chicken drumettes with garlic powder.
Beat egg; add milk.
Roll chicken in cornstarch, dip in egg-milk mixture and brown in hot oil.
Put browned wings in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pur brown sugar, vinegar, broth, catsup, soy sauce and bouillon in saucepan.
Bring to a boil until blended.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oriental pepper steak
directions: Over high heat, brown beef strips; push up to sides of pan. Mix garlic, sugar, ginger, 1/4 cup soy sauce and water.
Reduce to medium heat and add meat.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Increase to medium-high heat and add peppers and onions.
Stir-fry for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry to mix.
Add apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken-vegetable skillet
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Cut chicken in narrow strips.
Place in skillet; add garlic and cook over high heat, stirring often, about 3 minutes, until chicken is lightly browned.
Add frozen vegetables and cook about 2 minutes, stirring often, until thawed. Meanwhile, mix cornstarch, ginger, soy sauce and broth in a bowl until blended.
Pour into skillet; stir until sauce boils and thickens.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 minutes, until chicken is done.
Stir in peanuts.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into 1/4-inch strips.
Sprinkle with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Brown meat in butter.
Add garlic and broth.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and green peppers.
Cover and cook.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: biscuit pizza bake
directions: In skillet, cook beef over med. heat until it no longer is pink.
Meanwhile quarter the biscuits and place in a greased shallow 3 qt. baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce.
Drain beef and sprinkle over the biscuits and sauce.
Layer with green pepper, onion, mushrooms, pepperoni and cheeses.
Bake uncovered until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5-10 min. before serving.
Yields 6-8 servings.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Stir by hand all the ingredients.
Stir just until mixed.
Put into a floured and greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the corn and put into a large bowl.
Over low heat, stir oleo and brown sugar until boiling.
Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Pour onto two cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: savory slaw
directions: Break Ramen noodles into small pieces.
In large bowl, combine cabbage, noodles and sunflower seeds.
In a small bowl, combine the brown sugar, salt, wine vinegar, packet of soup seasoning and pepper.
Pour this over the cabbage mixture about 30 minutes before serving.

title: onion potato bake
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, milk and 1/2 can of onions in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt oleo and pour over the potatoes.
Top with salt and pepper and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hopscotch
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter in a double boiler. Add marshmallows and chow mein noodles.
Drop on wax paper and chill.

title: chocolate amaretto trifle
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan and divide cake into halves.
Prepare pudding using 1 1/2 cups milk plus 1/2 cup Amaretto.
Cut one-half of cake into 1 or 2-inch squares; layer in bowl.

Then add one-half of the pudding, one-half of the candy bars and one-half of the Cool Whip. Repeat with second half of cake, pudding, candy bars and Cool Whip. Refrigerate at least 5 or 6 hours or overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until batter is smooth. Pour batter into greased bread pan. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. After corn bread is done, spread margarine on top. Makes about 18 pieces.

title: chicken salad spread
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight, serve with Ritz crackers.

title: beef rolls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove 1 time each day for 3 days and knead well for 5 minutes. On fourth day, knead and divide into 6 or 7 balls and then roll into logs.
Bake in broiler pan for 9 hours at 160°.
After 4 1/2 hours, turn.
When done, drain on paper towels; cool.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook hamburger, onion and celery.
Drain. Pour 1 1/2 cups warm water over this.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and put in a baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Put chow mein noodles in; mix and bake 10 minutes more.

title: oven beef stew
directions: In 2-quart casserole combine beef, carrots, potatoes and celery.
In mixing bowl combine tomato sauce, dry soup mix, tapioca, bouillon, thyme and 1/4 cup water.
Stir in mixture. Cover; bake in 325° oven 1 hour.
Add green beans and bake 45 minutes or until beef and veggies are tender.

title: cream roll cookies
directions: Pulverize almonds in blender or work bowl of food processor fitted with steel blade.
Mix almonds, sugar, flour, egg whites and melted butter, beating until very well blended and egg whites are thoroughly incorporated.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Prepare cookie sheets by lining with aluminum foil and buttering heavily with soft butter.

Using 1 tablespoon of the mixture at a time, spread mixture on the cookie sheet into a 3 x 6-inch thin rectangle. Bake only 4 at a time at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or just until cookies are set and edges are lightly browned.
Cool for 5 seconds only.
Cookies become crisp quickly. Loosen each with a thin spatula or pancake turner and, while still warm, roll up loosely around handle of wooden spoon.
Remove cookie. Finish cooling on rack.
Repeat with remaining batter. Put chocolate into top of double boiler. Place over hot water and stir until melted.
Dip ends of cookies into chocolate.
Set aside to harden.
Whip the cream, sweetened with powder sugar and vanilla.
Put into pastry bag with star tip.
Pipe cream into both ends of each cookie, they need not be completely filled.

title: california blend casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until just tender according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly.
Heat soup, milk and cheese in saucepan until cheese is melted.
Pour over vegetables in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glorified brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and add oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix all together.
Add vanilla and stir in nuts.
Bake in sheet pan for 45 minutes.
While still hot (as soon as you get it out of the oven), put on a layer of miniature marshmallows.
Then top with icing.

title: klukie(polish dish)
directions: Mix the ingredients together and drop small dumplings into boiling water.
Drop all mixture into boiling water and continue to boil until they float.
Brown 1 tablespoon butter in another pan and pour over drained dumplings.
Serve with cottage cheese.

title: rice pudding(riskrem)
directions: Bring milk to a boil; add rice, vanilla and sugar.
Simmer over medium heat until cooked; or, if instant rice is used, cover and let stand 5 minutes over lowest heat.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin which has been softened in 1/4 cup cold water.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into a 2-quart mold; chill until set. Unmold and serve cold with a red sauce.

title: chicken "supream"
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place chicken in single layer in baking dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper and dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes.
Drain mushrooms and measure liquid, adding water to make 3/4 cup.
Combine Pream, flour, mushroom liquid, paprika and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir with wire whip until blended.
Add mushrooms and spoon over chicken.
Continue baking 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: meat loaf
directions: Crush corn flakes and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into a covered dish casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: black bottom twirls
directions: Divide butter among 12 muffin pans.
Combine topping and milk. Spoon about 1 teaspoon topping mixture into each pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Unroll crescent rolls to form 8 rectangles; press perforations to seal.
Spread rectangles with remaining topping mixture; sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Roll up, starting with short side.
Slice each into 3 rolls.
Place 2 rolls, cut side down, in each muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Loosen sides and invert.
Spoon any glaze remaining in pan over rolls.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pat in 9 x 15-inch pan.
Cover with catsup and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture; combine only enough to moisten.
Add blueberries mixed with sugar.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Mix chicken, cheese, onion and sour cream together.
Lay crescents out in 4 rectangles on cookie sheet.
Divide ingredients evenly on 4 rectangles.
Fold over and pinch shut with fork.
Beat 1 egg; brush over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: gumdrop bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to the combined the egg, milk and oil.
Add gumdrops and nuts.
Bake at 350° in greased loaf pan for 1 hour.
Makes 2 small or 1 large loaf.

title: spicy crackers
directions: Mix well.
In a 1 gallon jar put: 2 sleeves of crackers and half the canola oil mixture.
Roll jar.
Then add 2 sleeves crackers and remaining canola oil mixture.
Roll jar.
Continue to roll jar until the next day.

title: milnot cheese cake
directions: Cream together cheese and sugar.
Dissolve jello in hot water. Cool.
Add jello to first mixture.
Beat well.
Beat Milnot until stiff.
Fold into jello and cheese mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust, in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: spinach walnut salad
directions: In bowl, stir the tablespoon bacon fat, cottage cheese, vinegar, sugar and salt; drain cooked spinach and lightly press against colander to remove moisture. Place spinach in bowl or on plates; top with walnuts, then cottage cheese dressing. Crumble bacon over all.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Put everything in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth. Batter will be very thin.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Delicious!

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and quarter fruit.
Cut biscuits in half and roll or press out each biscuit half. Wrap quartered pieces of fruit with biscuit dough and place in baking dish.
Melt butter and pour over dumplings.	Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Combine hot water and sugar together until dissolved. Pour over dumplings and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 20 dumplings.
(Peaches may be substituted for apples.)

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add to cream mixture.
Add salt and flour with buttermilk, vanilla, soda and vinegar.
Do not overbeat, just blend.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix milk, half and half and rice and sugar.
Cook until rice is tender.
Mix eggs, vanilla and cinnamon in a bowl.
Cook raisins until plump.
Add egg mixture, along with drained raisins to pudding.
Keep stirring until mixture is thick and creamy. Spoon into dessert dishes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil hen with salt until tender.
Cut into small pieces. Combine in large bowl, cut up chicken and all remaining ingredients.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Beat eggs well with oil, sugar and pumpkin.
Add to dry mixture and mix thoroughly.
Bake in 3 small loaf pans at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until brown and springs back when touched lightly.

title: crescent apple quicks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir until apples are well coated.
Separate crescent dough into 16 triangles.
Spoon about 1 rounded tablespoonful apple mixture onto center of each triangle.
Fold 3 points of dough over filling, overlapping like an envelope.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: vodka slush
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender and freeze overnight. Serve in tall glasses. Mix with 7-Up, Squirt or Sprite.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until cooked.
Peel and cube potatoes. Coat and toss potatoes with French dressing.
Chill 2 hours.
Add eggs (chopped), salt, celery, onion, pepper and basil.
Mix mayo with milk until smooth.
Add to potato mixture.
Chill 2 hours.

title: veggie salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Put in bowl.
Pour the oil, sugar, vinegar and water over the vegetables and stir.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Stir again before serving.

title: cookie sheet party cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on pkg and bake in a cookie sheet.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice pudding
directions: In saucepan with tight fitting lid, put milk, honey, rice, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Heat to scalding using a whisk to beat mixture occasionally.
Cook, covered, over medium-low heat for about 1 hour, until rice is tender or milk is absorbed and mix is creamy, stirring about every 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix together in a small bowl the raisins, vanilla and liqueur or hot water; set aside.
During the last 10 minutes of cooking rice mix, fold raisin mixture in.
Transfer to a bowl; cover with plastic wrap until cool.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pudding and pineapple together.
Fold in marshmallows. Place in refrigerator until thickened.

title: good granola
directions: Combine the oats, coconut, milk, wheat germ, seeds and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together well.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on paper towels.
Eat for snack or breakfast.

title: sticky buns
directions: Take bread
dough
when ready to put in pans.
Roll out dough about
1 inch thick, spread margarine over dough; sprinkle cinnamon
and
brown sugar on dough and roll up like jelly roll and cut.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Mix eggs, vinegar, sugar, flour, salt, water and mustard in bowl.
In medium size saucepan, fry bacon.
Add the egg mixture and stir over heat until thickened (about 5 minutes).
This tastes good hot or cold.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook together for 5 to 6 minutes or until thickened the water, cornstarch and sugar.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Pour this over precooked pie shell that has been filled with fresh strawberries.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip or whip cream just before serving, if desired.

title: hamantashen
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Add oil and vanilla.
Add juice and rind.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into O shape using glass dipped in flour.
Put filling in center.
Fold over, one side to middle, other side to middle.
Pinch edges.
Brush with egg.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Heat together tomatoes and cheese in microwave.
Mix ingredients together well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: caramel pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Pour into baked crust and top with meringue made with 4 egg whites.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well with a spoon.
Add drained peaches (chopped).
Divide mixture in pie shells.
Refrigerate.
These pies can be made in 5 to 10 minutes and are out of this world.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break ground beef in small pieces while frying with chopped onions.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish.
Spread creamed corn over beef.
Spread whipped potatoes over corn.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine apples, sugar and cooking oil.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring often.
Scald raisins and let cool.
Mix flour and spices together.
Sprinkle a little flour over nuts and raisins and then combine.
Add flour mixture, eggs and vanilla to apple mixture. Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Put into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a glass loaf pan.
Spread catsup over top.
Cook, covered, with waxed paper 8 to 10 minutes on High.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potato chips.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add baking mix and spices.
Coat chicken pieces well.
Place chicken, skin sides down, in pan and bake, uncovered, at 425° for 35 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake, uncovered, until done, 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart pan in hot oil, brown roast on all sides.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low; cook for 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Gradually stir into soup mixture.

title: peanut butter-irish potato candy
directions: Boil potato in jacket until tender.
Cool a bit.
Peel and cream.
Add confectioners sugar to make stiff enough to roll on sugar sprinkled board. Roll out and spread with peanut butter. Roll up into long rolls.
Wrap in damp cloth and let sit (about 20 minutes or so).
Cut in thin slices.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat egg; add milk.
Sift rest of ingredients together.
Add egg and milk.
Pour into funnel while holding finger over bottom. Swirl batter into hot fat and fry until brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Optional:
Cheese, crackers on top, chopped and grated.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda and raisins; mix well.
Add oatmeal by stirring.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Pour lime mixture over cucumbers covering cucumbers completely. Soak 24 hours, then drain and rinse well.
Then soak 3 hours in ice water.
Drain and cover with following mixture and let set out overnight:
cider vinegar, sugar, salt, pickling spice and cloves. Next morning, put on stove over medium heat.
Bring to a boil. Boil 10 minutes.
Place in jars and seal.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and lemon juice; mix well.
Mix dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add apples to sugar and shortening mixture; then add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins last.
Bake 1 hour at 375° or until done when a toothpick comes out clean.

title: chopped suey cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well oiled 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange bread
directions: Combine sugar, pecans and orange rind in small bowl.
Separate each biscuit and pull apart into halves.
Place cream cheese square in center of biscuit half and place 2nd half on top of it, pinching sides together.
Dip in butter and dredge in sugar mixture.
Stand each biscuit on edge in lightly greased 12 cup Bundt pan or pound cake pan, spacing evenly.
Drizzle with remaining butter and sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately invert onto wire cooling rack.
Combine powdered sugar and orange juice. Spoon over warm bread.
Serve immediately.
Makes eight 10-inch coffee cake.

title: rolls
directions: Add yeast, salt, shortening, milk and egg.
Add flour.
Set 3 hours and then roll out.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 425°.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Put half of ham, potatoes and onions in slow cooker.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and cheese.
Repeat and add soup on top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or on high for 4 hours.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Fry until done.
Remove bacon and brown onion in fat.
Add beef, paprika, red pepper flakes, cooked bacon, tomatoes and rice.
Turn into greased casserole. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 5.

title: ma's baked custard
directions: Combine sugar, salt, eggs, hot milk and vanilla.
Pour into custard cups or baking pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° until custard is set.
Serves 4.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with cottage cheese.
Sprinkle green pepper, tomatoes and shredded Cheddar cheese over mixture. Spread taco sauce over top.
Serve with Ritz type crackers.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Make instant mashed potatoes for 8. Brown beef and onion together, drain, season with pepper and garlic powder.

title: crawfish fettuccine casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in butter.
Add flour. Cover and cook on low for 15 minutes.
Stir often.
Add parsley and crawfish.
Cook 15 minutes; stir often.
Add half and half, half of Velveeta, jalapeno and garlic.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 30 minutes, stirring often.
Add cooked noodles; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining Velveeta cubes and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: marinade for fish or meat(roast, steak, pork)
directions: Put all in Ziploc bag with meat.
May leave overnight, but at least 1 hour, turning often.

title: ham and chicken in noodle soup(4 servings)
directions: Sprinkle the chicken wings with the wine, salt and pepper. Steam for 20 minutes.
Cut the meat into thin strips or tear it into shreds with your hands.
Heat the stock and season with salt and pepper.
Cook the noodles in a generous amount of water. Drain and place in a warmed tureen or individual deep soup bowls. Pour the hot soup over the noodles.
Arrange the chicken, ham and snow peas on top and sprinkle with the green onion.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Add pineapple juice and fruit cocktail.
Add sherbet about 15 or 20 minutes before serving. Three recipes will serve 100 guests 7-ounce cups.

title: green bean supreme("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Cook and drain green beans.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble.
In 2 tablespoons bacon drippings in skillet, cook onion until tender.
Blend in soup, milk and beans. Put into casserole, top with bacon and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: husbands cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Combine soup with water and soda. Add to mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins or nuts.
Pour into 9-inch tube or large loaf pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat by hand until blended.
Add nuts and chips.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: grahams eclair
directions: Layer graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat banana pudding with milk until it thickens.
Fold container of whipped topping into banana pudding and pour over grahams.
Top with another layer of grahams and ice with chocolate icing, filling all cracks.
Refrigerate overnight or for several hours until grahams are soft.
Cut in small servings.
Rich!
Keep refrigerate until served.

title: low-fat baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and broccoli together.
Drain.
Set aside.
In saucepan, put in milk and heat.
Add salt, pepper and Molly McButter.
Thicken with the flour as you would for a cheese sauce. (Add cheese, while still hot.)
Put all in a casserole dish: cheese sauce, macaroni and broccoli.
Stir all together.
Sprinkle with your bread crumbs (3 slices white or wheat bread put on cookie sheet and baked until dry; crumble).

title: crustless quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients. Transfer to a 10 inch quiche pan coated with non-stick cooking spray.

title: turnaround turkey and rice
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add celery and onion and cook for 5 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add cooked turkey.
Blend water, gravy mix, milk, flour and season-all; pour over turkey mixture.
Stir.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: creamy coconut cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, oil, water and coconut in a large bowl.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched. Punch holes in cake with fork when cool.
Pour cream of coconut over cake.
Let cool.
Mix whipped topping with 1 1/2 cups coconut; frost cake.
Refrigerate.

title: old fashioned lemon sauce
directions: Combine in saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture comes to a boil.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: super egg bake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put together one day head.
Arrange bread in bottom of dish.
Spread meat over bread.
Pour eggs over this and sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: o's, nuts and raisins
directions: Put O's, nuts and raisins in large bowl.
In a saucepan, add all the rest of ingredients, except soda.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Pour foamy mixture over cereal, nuts and raisins; mix until coated.
Put in shallow pan; bake for 10 minutes at 250°.
Store in a tight container.
Great snack on bus to and from band competitions.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cold water and chill.
Add strawberries.
Dissolve other package jello in 1 cup boiling water; chill.
Mix with Cool Whip and dump on top of first part.

title: 20 minute meal variety
directions: This is a variety package of recipes for chicken (either pieces or cutlets, fat or thin) or pork chops (any style).
Use any amount you want and increase or decrease sauces accordingly. All amounts are estimates and will need to be adjusted according to taste and desired amount of sauce.

title: seven-layer jello salad
directions: Bring the milk and sugar to a boil.
Add Knox gelatine dissolved in 1/2 cup cold water.
Let cool.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Dissolve each package of jello in 1 cup hot water and add 1/2 cup cold water.
Place one layer of jello in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
When set, add 1 1/2 cups white mixture.
Dissolve next color jello and when white mixture is set, place on top.
Continue with 1 1/2 cups white mixture, next jello, etc.
Makes a very pretty and delicious salad.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add shortening and cream together.
Add egg and orange juice; mix until moistened.
Fold in cranberries.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool.

title: penny-pinching casserole
directions: Cook pepper (green) and fresh (if used) mushrooms and onions, too, until tender, not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring until mix is smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Combine 2 cups of the sauce with the rice.
Spread rice mix evenly in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan (buttered).
Make 8 nests in the rice with back of spoon.
Break eggs (one at a time) into a cup and put in a nest.
Cover eggs with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until eggs are cooked as you like.
Makes 4 to 8 servings.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Heat syrup and sugar to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add cornflakes and stir together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in ovenproof serving dish. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with party crackers (Wheat Thins are great!).
Enjoy!

title: honey buns
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in cake pan in oven.
Mix together melted butter, cinnamon and sugar in cake pan.
Cut biscuits into fourths and lay over mixture in cake pan.
Place in oven and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool 5 minutes.
Flip out on plate, cut and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix apples with dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add brown sugar and oatmeal to flour mixture.
Cut butter into mixture.
Mix with hands until it resembles meal.
Press 2/3 of mixture into 8-inch square pan.
Spread preserves over mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top and press down gently.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: crusty pizza dish
directions: Unroll 1 package dough, leaving seams intact.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown ground beef and onion until meat is done. Spread over dough.
Combine sauce, oregano and cheese; spread over meat.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add sifted dry ingredients and applesauce alternately.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Prepare jello with 3 3/4 cups liquid (juice from berries and water).
When almost set, whip jello for 10 minutes, placing dish with jello in ice water while you whip.
Add berries and marshmallows and gently fold in whipped cream.
Break cake into 1-inch pieces and place one layer of cake in bottom of tube pan. Pour layer of jello mixture over cake.
Then put another layer of cake and another layer of jello. Chill overnight.
Turn out of pan and frost with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Serve immediately.

title: tom and jerry batter
directions: In bowl, beat egg whites until stiff. Add salt.
In second bowl, beat egg yolks until light.
In another bowl, cream butter with powdered sugar and mix until crumbly.
Add egg yolks and flavorings.
Mix well.
Add spices and egg whites.
Beat until well mixed. Batter will keep for several weeks in refrigerator. May be frozen, covered, for several months.

title: sausage bread(breakfast food or party food)
directions: After dough rises, roll out into rectangle.
Fry sausage and drain.
Sprinkle 1/2 of sausage over dough.
Shred hot pepper cheese and mix with Mozzarella and parsley.
Spread this mixture over sausage already spread on bread dough.

title: cheese and onion pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup butter.
Press evenly into 9-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter until tender, not brown.
Spread onions over crust.

title: soap
directions: Stir together first four ingredients in the evening and let stand overnight in crock or granite pan.

title: colie's potluck special(chili)
directions: Brown ground beef.
Put kidney beans (drained), stewed tomatoes and seasoning in pot to simmer.
Add beef.

title: chicken fantasia
directions: Pound chicken lightly to make cutlets 1/4-inch thick.
Place a slice of ham on each cutlet; tuck in sides and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Skewer or tie.
In large skillet, slowly brown chicken in butter.
Stir in water, preserves, vinegar, salt and dry mustard. Cook uncovered for 20 minutes.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup. Blend cornstarch and reserved syrup.
Stir cornstarch mixture and pineapple into sauce in skillet; cook uncovered for 15 minutes until chicken is tender.
Turn chicken rolls once.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Blend in sugar and oil.
Add flour.
Stir all together; let rise 10 to 15 minutes.
Should be doubled.
Punch down and either make loaf or roll into rolls.
Let rise again 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook in 350° oven until brown.

title: oklahoma dip
directions: Mix hamburger, sausage and onion.
Brown in frying pan.
In a crock-pot melt tomatoes and cheeses.
Add meat and onion, mix well and keep warm in crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: gooseberry, red currant or sour cherry wine
directions: Heat berries in quart of water to boiling point (do not boil). Stir occasionally.
Let cool.
Put sugar into jar.
Add berries and water until almost to the neck (not full).
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cover with a white cloth and tie with a string or rubber band to make sure no fruit or vinegar flies get in.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs, onions and mushrooms; put in an 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Heat soup and pour over top.
Sprinkle grated cheese over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: coleslaw
directions: To the amount of grated cabbage needed for one's family, add the following: small amount of miniature marshmallows, diced apple, Spanish peanuts and some raisins, if desired. Add enough coleslaw dressing to make the salad fairly moist.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain. Remove from heat and add mixed vegetables, cheese, onion and bell pepper. Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and a dash of Worcestershire sauce.

title: arizona skillet dinner
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add onions, peppers, garlic, chili powder, salt and cumin.
Saute for 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes, kidney beans and corn.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Toss with elbows.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken pasta parmesan
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, cook chicken and onion in hot oil until chicken is browned and onion is tender.
Stir in soup, milk and sherry.
Add mushrooms, broccoli and Parmesan cheese. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: dinah's punch
directions: In a bowl, place ice cream and sherbet.
Pour in soda.
After mixing slightly, add ice cubes to keep cool.
Add vodka.

title: face paint
directions: You will also need a muffin tin.

title: no bean chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Saute onions, add remaining ingredients and return beef to pan.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: quick hash brown casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together, except for corn flakes and 1/2 stick margarine.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes which have been mixed with 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
This freezes well, but don't put topping on to freeze.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Mix all together and spread into pie dish.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: walnut crescents
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and flavoring.
Add dry ingredients; mix well, then chill.
Form into small crescents.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Serves 5 dozen.

title: swedish meat balls #3
directions: Mix very well all of the ingredients, except the butter for frying and the cream, in the order in which they are listed. Using the large end of a melon ball maker, form into tiny meat balls.
Saute the meat balls in the butter until they are well browned.
Shake the pan from side to side so that they roll and brown evenly on all sides.
Pour off any excess drippings which may accumulate during the frying.
Stir in the cream; simmer for 20 minutes, or until the sauce is thickened.
Serve with boiled potatoes or with broad noodles.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat shortening in skillet and brown beef and onion, discarding fat.
Combine all ingredients and simmer; or cook in crock-pot on low for 8 to 10 minutes, or on high for 5 hours, or on automatic 6 hours.
Yield: 4 to 5 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup beet juice to make it thicker.

title: elegant potatoes au gratin
directions: Boil, peel, cool and shred potatoes. Shred cheese.
Alternate layers of potatoes and cheese in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour whipping cream over potatoes and cheese.
Mix bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In frying pan, cook sausage until brown, breaking up as you cook.
Drain.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased pizza pan (12-inch) with points toward the center. Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations of dough.
Spoon meat over crust, sprinkle with hash browns and top with cheese.
In bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: norwegian gold cake
directions: Cream softened butter with flour (5 minutes). Add eggs, one at a time. Sift sugar, baking powder and salt and add to batter. Beat 2 minutes. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add salt, then add macaroni.
Cook for approximately 20 minutes (do not overcook).
Drain water, but leave some.
Chop Velveeta and let melt.
Add butter and pepper. Should be a little juicy.
Pour half into a 9 x 12-inch dish and add a layer of grated Cheddar cheese.
Pour remaining macaroni and top with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Put in 350° oven and bake just until it bubbles.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper and bring to boil. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Drain beans.
Add other vegetables as desired.

title: leczo
directions: 1. Cut the sausages, peppers and onions.
The pieces should be about 1 centimeter thick.

title: favorite cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together, then stir in flour, soda and salt.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon and set aside on paper towels to drain.
In a large bowl, combine broccoli, raisins, sunflower seeds and onion.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Spoon over broccoli mixture and toss to coat.
Sprinkle with chopped bacon and toss again.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
When ready to serve, add 1/2 cup pecans, 3 sliced bananas and 1 cup marshmallows.

title: chicken pepper souffle
directions: Mix chicken, soup, milk, onion and chilies in saucepan and heat on stove.
Line baking dish with Fritos.
Pour mixture over chips. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: baked chicken in sauce
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with dried beef.
Wrap each breast with two slices partially fried bacon.
Put chicken on top of dried beef.
Mix soup, sour cream and sherry and pour over chicken.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 3 hours at 275°, uncovered.

title: broccoli and tomato salad
directions: Mix tops of broccoli and cut up tomatoes.
Squeeze lemon juice over all.
Add pinch of garlic salt and mix thoroughly.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Add 1 bottle Green Goddess dressing and mix.
Let stand for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Before serving, sprinkle bacon bits over all ingredients and mix.
Serve.

title: danish cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Put nuts in flour and add to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop on cookie sheet with small spoon and flatten with bottom of glass dipped in water (so cookie doesn't stick to glass).
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Eat and enjoy.

title: louisiana fudge candy
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan and set aside.
Blend together thoroughly in a 3 quart pan the sugar, syrup and cream.
Bring to a
boil,
stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to soft ball (234°);
remove
from
heat
and
let cool five minutes. Blend in flour and beat until it is creamy and thick, about 15 minutes. Stir
in
pecans
and pour in pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: big texas pie
directions: Layer pie filling, pineapple, cake mix, coconut, nuts and margarine in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: king's arm's sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes.
Stir in all ingredients except 2 tablespoons of sugar. Turn mixture into prepared casserole and sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake at 400°
for 30 minutes.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger and pork sausage.
Add onions, celery and water to meat and simmer until soft.
Add chow mein vegetables, mushrooms and soy sauce to meat mixture and bring to a boil. Thicken with cornstarch and water.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray dish with Pam.
In saucepan, heat sauce and water.
Combine Ricotta cheese, 2 cups Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Pour 3/4 cup sauce in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange 3 pieces uncooked pasta lengthwise over sauce. Pour 1/2 cup sauce over pasta; spread with half cheese mixture. Cover with 1/2 cup sauce.
Repeat layers.

title: sportsman's sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order as listed.
Be sure lettuce is dry.
Do not add salt or pepper.
It wilts the lettuce.
Do not mix or stir; it stirs itself when served.

title: liz's jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all; blend well.
Put in jelly jar and refrigerate. This will keep indefinitely.
Pour over 8 ounce package cream cheese and serve with Wheat Thin crackers.

title: birthday cake
directions: Generously grease a 9 x 13-inch spring-form cake pan. Cut a piece of waxed paper to fit the bottom of the pan. Place waxed paper on greased bottom, then grease the paper.
Lightly dust pan with flour; set aside.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Toss apples with lemon juice in small bowl.
Arrange apples in overlapping circle in a buttered 9-inch pan.
Drizzle maple syrup over apples.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in butter.
Texture should be large crumbs.
Scatter the mixture over the apples as if making a crust. Bake 30 minutes or until top is crisp.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: black magic cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or two 9 x 1-inch cake pans.
Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Sift.
Add eggs, coffee, buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes (batter will be thin).
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with favorite vanilla icing.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in blender; pour over next 4 ingredients.
I prefer the 1 pound spinach.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, 2/3 cup crackers, salt and pepper.
Stir in corn, onion and pimiento; mix well.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Toss butter with remaining crackers; sprinkle on top of corn mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs and margarine and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mixture will be very stiff.
Set aside.

title: lydia's tom thumb bars
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening and brown sugar.
Stir in flour. Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite-size pieces.
This usually takes about 2 months.
Add enough gravy to cover (approximately 500 gallons).
Cook over kerosene fire 5 weeks at 450°.
This will serve 4000 people.
If more are expected, the rabbits may be added but only if necessary as most people don't like to find a hare in their stew!!!!!!

title: missy's chicken divan
directions: You can make this any size, depending on how much you have for ingredients.
Layer the bottom of a casserole dish with the crackers.
Cover the crackers with a layer of cooked chicken. Drain the cooked vegetables and put on top of chicken.
Cover vegetables with layer of cooked stuffing.
Pour the gravy or cream of chicken soup on top of the stuffing.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, until bubbling and brown.

title: meat pies
directions: Saute.
Drain off fat.
Add about 1 tablespoon of flour; set aside.

title: slushy punch
directions: Mix and pour into jugs.
Place in freezer.
Shake every 20 minutes until slushy.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda into pan.
Mix oil, vinegar and vanilla into dry ingredients.
Pour cold water over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool.
Frost as desired.

title: chicken chili lite
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over low heat for about 20 to 25 minutes. Add water, if needed, during cooking.
About 8 servings with less than 1 gram of fat per serving.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll onto floured board and cut into strips.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Shape into balls and brown in skillet.
After brown on all sides, put into boiling water 5 to 10 minutes.
Will rise to top when done.
Remove from water and add to sauce.
Let simmer until ready to serve.

title: sugar rhubarb muffins
directions: Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and milk, mixing until moistened well.
Fold in rhubarb.
Fill paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove. Place on rack to cool.
Yields approximately 1 dozen.

title: cranberry fluffy fruit
directions: Combine cranberries and marshmallows; add sugar.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, nuts and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Turn into a serving bowl or spoon into individual lettuce cups.
Trim with a cluster of green grapes, if desired.

title: salmon loaf casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well and place in a greased dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: honey mustard dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups. Serve with chips, vegetables or over lettuce wedge.

title: grandmother's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix well and pour into ice cream freezer canister. Follow ice cream freezer directions.

title: cheese and green chili sandwich
directions: Mix with enough salad dressing or mayonnaise to spread on bread.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Wrap each breakfast steak (very thin) around a slice of bacon and a slice of onion.
Secure with toothpick.
Pour beef bouillon over.
Cook in crock-pot or simmer over low heat until steaks are fork-tender.
Thicken gravy and add mushrooms.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: dirt cups
directions: Will need clear plastic cups

title: czechoslovakian goulash
directions: N.B.:
Can make your own of the last 3 ingredients, if desired.

title: basic spaghetti sauce
directions: Peel and cut tomatoes into small pieces.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Put into blender for 10 seconds; return to pot.
Saute onion, pepper, celery and garlic just until onion is transparent. Add to tomatoes.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and spices.
Cover and simmer at least 1 hour, longer if you can as the flavor improves the longer it cooks.
Taste and add more seasonings if needed.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Form into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place in airtight container.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar and cream mixture.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Pour into pie shells.
Pour pie filling on top.
Chill.

title: haystacks
directions: You will need wax paper or cupcake holders.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Saute almonds in margarine.
Sprinkle on top and bake 3 to 5 minutes longer. Serve with crackers.

title: hula cake
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 inch pan and bake at 300° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: auburn chocolate fondue
directions: Melt chocolate. Add honey and cream. Stir until melted. Add liqueur. Serve with fruits (strawberries, bananas) or pound cake cut in small cubes.

title: molded corned beef-cheese loaf
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
Place over boiling water and stir until gelatine is dissolved.
Add salt, lemon juice and Tabasco.
Cool.
Gradually stir into mayonnaise.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 6 cup loaf pan.

title: fried fruit pies
directions: Sift
flour
and
salt together.
Cut in shortening and mix with hands.
Add water.
Roll out about 1/8 inch thick on floured board.
Cut
4-inch sections and add fruit, then fold and press edges together.
Fry in deep fat.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and blot excess water with paper towels.
Blend dry ingredients on platter and dredge chicken pieces.
Arrange on baking pan.
Whisk together lime juice and olive oil.
Drizzle over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes, depending on size of pieces.

title: oven apple butter
directions: Mix ingredients and place in 400° oven.
Cook for 2 1/2 hours. This is supposed to cook slow and oven temperature should be cut down if bubbling and cooking too fast.

title: upcountry shells
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cheese, bacon bits, onion flakes, garlic salt and parsley in medium mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise to mixture and stir.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Smash cream cheese against bowl with fork.
Add milk, sugar, cream and vanilla.
Add one egg at a time while beating.
Beat until a little lumpy.
Pour into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (or until golden brown).
It will be watery. Allow to cool for 1 hour at room temperature.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix together crackers, pecans and cereal; pour oil over cereal mixture and then dry Ranch dressing.
Stir and mix well.
Put in shallow pan.
Cook at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Good for holidays.

title: fruit strata salad
directions: Mix and chill. May use additional melons (watermelon, cantaloupe).

title: quick dessert
directions: For a group over 6 I double the recipe.

title: almond cream confections
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cocoa, vanilla, salt and eggs in a heavy
saucepan;
cook
over low heat, stirring
constantly until butter melts and mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from heat; add almonds and wafer crumbs.
Stir well.
Press firmly into ungreased
9-inch
square pan.
Cover and chill.
Spread cream filling over almond mixture; cover and chill.
Cut into squares. Remove
from
pan.	Drizzle
chocolate
over
Cream Filling.

title: cake-mix cookies
directions: Beat eggs well; add water.
Add to cake mix; blend well. Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° on greased baking sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients with shortening.
Soften yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Mix well; set in refrigerator until ready to use.
This will keep one week.
Roll out ahead at least 30 minutes.
Brush with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cloud nine
directions: Mix the ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth. Serves 1 person.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese; add Worcestershire sauce.
Chop onions and dried beef and add.
Shape into a ball.
Cool for 24 hours.

title: mandarin orange jello mold
directions: It is now fairly established that the common wart, which is so unsightly and often proliferous on the hands and face can be easily removed by small doses of sulphate magnesia taken internally.

title: harvest grape pie
directions: Remove and save skin from grapes by pinching grapes at end opposite the stem (pulp pops out).
Put the pulp in a saucepan (do not add water); bring to a rolling boil.
While mixture is hot, rub through strainer or food mill to remove seeds.
Mix strained pulp with reserved grape skins.
Combine sugar and flour; mix lightly with grape mixture.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and salt. Pour into pastry shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust or top with pastry cut outs.
If using a full top crust, cut slits and seal and flute edges.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes or until
top crust is brown and juice thickens.
Serve cool.

title: salt-free seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: * Use Ragu extra-thick and zesty spaghetti sauce.

title: pineapple walnut cake
directions: Combine flour and baking soda; set aside. Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and pineapple. Add mixture to flour and baking soda, mixing well. Add nuts and mix again. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Chop vegetables (fairly small pieces).
In 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased) spread dough all on the bottom and up sides, about 1/2 inch.
Bake at 375° for approximately 13 to 15 minutes or until brown; cool.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in 1 tablespoon of butter until tender.
Add ground round and brown on low heat.
Add rice until lightly brown.
Blend can of tomatoes into small pieces and add to meat mixture.
Add Tabasco sauce and simmer about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: snowman crispies
directions: Line a baking sheet with wax paper and coat with nonstick cooking spray.
In a microwave safe bowl, heat butter and marshmallows on high for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring at the halfway point.
Stir until smooth.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Boil cabbage and drain.
Place in casserole in layers (first the cabbage, then the cream sauce, then the grated cheese), until all are used up.
Be sure there is a layer of cheese on the top. Run in a 400° oven until bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and cocoa and blend thoroughly to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts. Spread mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: country corn bread stuffing
directions: In small skillet saute celery and onion until tender.
In large bowl combine celery mixture, corn bread, bread cubes, sausage and sage; mix well.
Add broth, water and eggs.
Toss lightly until bread is thoroughly moistened.
(Add 1/2 cup additional water if more moist dressing is desired.) Lightly spoon stuffing into body cavity and neck region of turkey.
Truss and roast according to standard roasting directions.
Makes enough stuffing for one turkey (about 3 quarts of stuffing).

title: sardines made from smelt
directions: Pack fish in pint jars.
Add 1/2 teaspoon canning salt to each jar.
Pour sauce over fish in jars; seal.
Process in pressure cooker for 50 minutes at 10 pounds.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onions.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix with other ingredients, except cheese and sausage.
Top with cheese and sausage cut thin.
