Bake until cheese melts through noodles. (One-half recipe makes a large casserole.)

title: topping for sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Turn off heat.
Add oats, brown sugar and pecans.
Stir all ingredients together and spread over casserole. Bake at 350° until crispy, 15 minutes (plus).
Remove and let stand uncovered.
Serve.

title: easy-to-roll pie dough
directions: Mix together flour and Crisco. Beat egg in measuring cup and fill to line with milk.
Makes 5 dough balls.
Freezes very well. Can be thawed quickly in microwave.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, salt and celery and mustard seed to a boil; add oil.
Pour over cabbage and onion.
Let stand, covered, in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Keeps well.

title: hearty oat and walnut bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2
cups
flour, oats, brown sugar, 1 tablespoon margarine, salt and
yeast	in
a
large bowl.
Stir in water; beat on medium
speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Stir
in
nuts
and enough of the remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn
greased
side up.
Cover;
let rise in warm place for
1 hour.
Grease
large
cookie sheet.
Punch down dough; divide
in half.
Shape
each half into round loaf.
Place on cookie
sheet. Brush
with
softened butter.
Cover; let rise for	30 minutes or until double.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Remove from sheets to cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: Add all ingredients together, except bananas, marshmallows and sour cream.
Add these right before serving.

title: tostados
directions: Fry tortillas on both sides in hot oil until crisp.
Drain well on paper towels.
Spread tortillas generously with refried beans, then meat filling.
Add lettuce, tomato and avocado.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; top with sour cream.
Add pickled chili slices and olives.
Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 8 g, protein 13 g, fat 28 g, calories 336.
One serving = 2 meat medium fat exchanges, 1 vegetable exchange, 3 fat exchange.

title: chicken parmesan and roasted potatoes
directions: Rinse chicken; shake in bag with bread crumbs.
Lay in baking pan.
Cut potatoes in chunks.
Put in the end of pan.
Drizzle potatoes with a little oil.
Cover chicken and potatoes with sauce and garlic powder.
Cover with foil; bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove foil; sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: Cook the ground beef with the onion; drain good and put in crock-pot. Add the remaining ingredients. Be sure all your meat is cut up small and your tomatoes are mashed up. I use Mexican tomatoes, but it makes it hot. If you don't like it hot, use regular stewed tomatoes and regular ketchup. Simmer in the crock-pot for about 8 hours on low. You can simmer it on top of stove if you are in a hurry. This freezes real good. It also makes 6 quarts.

title: grandma buchanan's sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and Crisco.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Mix together and add the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Chill dough overnight or several hours.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in flour.
Top with a raisin in the middle and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In large mixing bowl put flour, sugar, salt, vanilla, almond extract, oil and eggs.
Turn mixer to medium speed; blend until smooth.
Bake in angel food cake pan that has been greased and floured at 300° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Cook milk, flour, salt, egg and sweetener until mixture coats spoon.
Add softened gelatin and vanilla.
Whip evaporated milk until thick.
Fold into custard mixture.
Chill and freeze in ice cream freezer.
Yields:
1 quart; 16 calories per ounce.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in pan according to directions.
Combine all ingredients in bowl; toss gently to mix well.
Cover; refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: my best cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla well together.
Add pineapple and juice.
Mix.
Then add soda, flour and nuts; mix as you add.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
After 35 minutes, do toothpick test.

title: jungle fun toss
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Store in airtight container.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Beat yolks thoroughly and add dry mustard powder, lemon juice, salt, pepper, garlic powder and then slowly, very slowly 1 cup of olive oil (all ingredients at room temperature) while vigorous beating is going on all the time.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients.
Put vanilla wafer in bottom of each paper cup.
Fill 1/2 full with cream cheese mixture. Bake 12 minutes at 375°. Cool. Top with cherry pie filling.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: *Creamed corn is good, too.

title: west virginia mountain lasagna
directions: In sheet pan, cover bottom with sauce, 1 layer of noodles, sauce, Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese (4 spoonfuls), Mozzarella cheese (3 slices) and repeat layers until pan is almost full. Cook at 350° until cheese melts.
Don't cover.
Makes 2 pans.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss together and add 1 bag of crushed tortilla chips before serving.
Top with Catalina salad dressing.

title: sue's potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes, put in 4-quart pan along with chopped onion, celery and grated carrots.
Just barely cover with water. Boil until potatoes are just barely done.
Reduce heat.
Add butter and evaporated milk.
Mix flour with a little water or save enough milk to mix with.
Add flour mixture to potatoes.
Add cubed Velveeta.
Let it melt and salt and pepper to taste.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: In a skillet, over medium heat, cook mushrooms and onion in butter until mushrooms are lightly browned, six to eight minutes. Spread mushroom mixture evenly in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese over mushroom mixture.
Beat together remaining ingredients, until they are well blended.
Pour over mushroom mixture and cheese.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then salad dressing and water.
Add soda last.
Bake at about 375°.

title: pan tarts
directions: Add 1/2 the batter in long greased pan; add 1 can of fruit and cover with the rest of the batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: uncle chuck's blackberry wine
directions: Boil 1 gallon of water with 3 pounds of sugar to thin syrup stage.
Mash berries.
When syrup is cooled to lukewarm, add raisins and yeast and add to mashed berries.
Stir, then cover with cloth and let stand for 7 days in a warm place.
Then skim off top scum and strain liquid through several layers of cheesecloth.
Cover and let stand until fermenting stops, about 3 or 4 days.
Skim off top again.
Ladle into bottles, cork and store in a cool place for several weeks.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water. Add all other ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add eggs and beat 3 minutes.
Drain off 1/2 cup juice from can of fruit cocktail and add the rest of the can of fruit cocktail to the batter.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle over the top before baking, 1 cup brown sugar and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: fresh cauliflower(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Combine ingredients. Add to cauliflower that has been broken into bite-size pieces. Marinate overnight.

title: broiled reuben sandwiches
directions: Combine mayonnaise and chili sauce, stirring well.
Spread butter on one side of each slice of bread; spread other side with mayonnaise mixture.
Arrange cheese, corned beef and sauerkraut on mayonnaise side of 6 slices of bread.
Top with remaining, buttered side out.
Place sandwiches on a cookie sheet and broil each side until browned.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: macaroons
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add sugar slowly, beating well after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Fold coconut and cracker crumbs into egg white.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 20 minutes.
Yields 18 to 24 cookies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased baking dish (9 x 13-inches).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until golden brown.
Grated cheese may be added a short time before it is done.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs. Remove yolks from white mash yolks. Add miracle whip onions and pepper mix well. Spoon in egg whites. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine in a saucepan water, sugar and shortening.
Boil for 5 minutes; cool.

title: graham cracker lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with peas; top with diced chicken.
Pour chicken and rice soup over this.
Mix cream of chicken with broth from cooked chicken; mix Stove Top. Cover the casserole with this.
Add more broth if needed to keep moisture.
Cook at 400° for about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together with wooden spoon for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
When cool, remove from pans and glaze all sides with pastry brush.

title: toffee
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, water and Karo in 2-quart saucepan. Cook on medium heat until it reaches hard crack (290°) on candy thermometer.
Pour in 3/4 cup of almonds and mix.
Pour on large cookie sheet.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Lay Hershey bars on top. Spread Hershey bars as they melt.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup almonds on top of Hershey bars.
Refrigerate for 1 1/2 hours. Break into pieces.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, seasonings, sour cream, cheese and onions. Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Mix crushed corn flakes with melted butter (enough corn flakes to soak up butter). Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: giant cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spread in pan (greased).
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until brown at 300°.
This is enough to make 2 pans.
Spread the dough thin.

title: sweet morsels
directions: Melt chocolate morsels over hot water.
Cool to room temperature.
Gently stir in cereal until well coated; drop by tablespoonful on waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator until chocolate is set, dry and hard, about 2 hours.

title: pancakes
directions: Measure flour into bowl and stir in sugar. Beat egg separately. Add egg, milk and all to flour. Stir until smooth. May need to add a small amount of milk or flour to be thin enough to pour on a greased hot grill or skillet.
Makes 12 to 16 small pancakes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Press in baking dish the flour, margarine and pecans.
Cook for about 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
This is the first 3 ingredients.
Spread on top of cooled crust the mixture of cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread 2 cans blueberry pie filling on top of this mixture.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt in one bowl.
In another bowl mix remainder of ingredients.
Mix together and pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: eggie soup
directions: In a large pot, boil chicken or chicken parts, onion, celery and parsley.
Take out chicken from broth before you stir in the veggies.

title: cole slaw to freeze
directions: Boil the sugar, oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef in pan for 7 to 8 minutes; set aside.
In boiling water, cook rice and chicken noodle soup mix. Add onion, bell pepper and celery stalks.
Mix all together in a casserole.
Bake covered at 400° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Mix all ingredients and put in casserole.
Top with half package of Pepperidge Farm dressing and 1/2 cup oleo.
Bake in oven at 350` for 30 minutes.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Roll 20 Ritz crackers.
Beat egg whites; add sugar.
Fold crackers into beaten egg whites with baking powder and salt.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Place in greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: straw-nana pie
directions: Slice bananas and strawberries; arrange to cover bottom of each crust.
In medium mixing bowl, beat the Cool Whip, cream cheese, vanilla and sugar until fluffy.
Pour 1/2 the mixture into each crust.
Pour 1 jar of strawberry topping on each pie; spread to cover top.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: cheese quesadillas
directions: Mix cheese and onions.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture on the center of each tortilla; fold over.
Spray a large skillet with cooking spray. Can be cooked on a George Foreman grill.

title: marti's veggie soup
directions: Combine
beef or turkey and onion in large
Dutch
oven and brown; drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer
3 hours. Stir occasionally.
Freezes great!
Can substitute any frozen vegetables your family likes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Put drained peaches in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle lemon rind over top.
Mix brown sugar with dry Jiffy mix. Sprinkle on top of peaches.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer as listed.
Cover with 2 cups mayonnaise.
Toss before serving.
Best if made 12 hours before serving.

title: surprise kisses
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour and nuts; blend well.
Remove foil from candy.
Shape 1 tablespoon dough around each kiss, covering completely.
Place on Pamed cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken chalupa
directions: Cook and debone chicken; chop chicken into small pieces.
Add cream of chicken soup, green chili peppers, Monterey Jack cheese, sour cream and 1/2 pound of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix together in a large bowl.
Stuff tortilla shells with mixture; roll shells and place them in a 9 x 12 baking dish.
Cover with the remaining soup mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 pound of Cheddar cheese over the top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover to brown cheese top.

title: play clay
directions: Put flour and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Measure water; add food coloring, then oil to water and food coloring.
Mix together.
Slowly pour water and oil mixture into flour and salt. Mix well.
Knead mixture for 3 or 4 minutes.
Put clay on table. Pull, push, stretch and squeeze 2 to 3 minutes more.
Divide into 3 equal parts.
Play with 1 part and put other parts in plastic bag.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Cook pasta; drain, cool and combine with remaining ingredients.
Add dressing and refrigerate several hours.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers and remove any seeds.
Mix meat, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Stuff peppers 3/4 full with this mixture. Stand up in a deep skillet with a lid.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the peppers.
Cover and cook slowly 40 minutes.
Add a small amount of water if necessary.
Serve hot.

title: radish and egg salad
directions: Wash and slice radishes thinly.
Mix with green onions, sour cream and salt.
Place in salad bowl; garnish with chopped or diced hard-boiled eggs and dill.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Shred chipped beef into bottom of 10 x 12-inch shallow casserole, greased.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each chicken breast.
Place the breasts on top of the chipped beef. Sprinkle with pepper.
Blend the soup with the sour cream and pour over the chicken breasts.
Cover and bake for 3 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut and arrange cabbage in bottom of casserole dish.
Season to taste.
Brown hamburger meat and onion and spread over cabbage. Add rice, tomatoes and soup.
Cover and cook until done.
You may cook in microwave.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Add sugar, lemon rind and juice.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Crush vanilla wafers and put into bottom of Pyrex dish.
Remove frozen Pet milk from freezer and whip until very creamy.
Fold together all ingredients and pour over vanilla wafers.
Chill several hours.

title: healthy garden dip
directions: Combine cottage cheese and sour cream.
Finely chop vegetables and add to mixture.
Season with a dash of each of the spices. Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups of dip.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up hen and cook by boiling until tender.
Remove from broth and debone.
Cut meat into small pieces.
Sift flour into a pan Make well in flour; add the shortening and mix with water to make about 3 cups of dough stiff enough to roll out on floured surface with rolling pin.
Roll as thin as possible.
Cut into small 1 inch squares.
Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Drop dumplings and butter into broth.
Stir in chicken.
Cover and cook on simmer until done. If you use a fryer instead of a hen, add several bouillon cubes for a richer broth.
These have always been a favorite at homecomings.

title: rio grande dip
directions: Place half the beans and salsa in a blender container.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Repeat with remaining beans and salsa.
Spoon beat mixture into a 9-inch pie plate.
Top with chilies, tomato and green onion.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Top with cheese; bake 5 minutes more.
Serve with tortilla chips. Yields 10 to 12.

title: london town gratitude punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use 2 tablespoons per cup of boiling water.
Two ounces rum may optionally be added per cup.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and parsley. Form in a roll. Mix pecans and parsley together.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve with crackers.

title: zabaglione
directions: Beat yolks and sugar until well blended. Stir in Marsala or sherry. Place mixture in large bowl and place over medium heat. Whisk constantly while cooking until texture is thick (being very, very careful not to curdle). Pour over fresh fruit.

title: chicken or turkey pot pie
directions: Combine chicken broth and vegetables in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir in chicken soup and pepper.
Spoon into baking dish; set aside.
Combine flour, milk and melted butter.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rolls
directions: Prepare yeast; set aside.
Mix 1 cup boiling water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Add yeast (dissolved) and beaten egg.
Mix; add 4 cups flour.
Mix well.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Trim as much fat off brisket as possible.
Put in 2-inch deep pan.
Pour 1 to 2 bottles of barbecue sauce over brisket.
Cook at 275° for 6 to 8 hours.
Turn once after 2 hours.
Drain off most of the sauce.
Cut in 3/8-inch strips and pour a little barbecue sauce over the brisket.
Serve and enjoy!

title: cornbread cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased muffin pan.
Put in enough oil so that it will come on top of batter.
Bake at 450° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes or until real brown and crisp. Muffins can be cooked on broil.
Just make sure they don't burn.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix with spoon until well mixed.
Take 1 teaspoon at a time and roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on cookie sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: saucepan fudge cake
directions: In medium sized saucepan, place water, chocolate and butter. Let them melt; stir and cool.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder and add to first mixture.
Add sugar and buttermilk and last, the eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pans for 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes great cupcakes; very moist!

title: pecan pie
directions: In blender mix together the first five ingredients and blend well.

title: basque chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces (or use 6 boned breasts). Arrange in greased 3-quart casserole.
Lightly brown rice, garlic and onions in oil.
Add tomatoes and seasonings and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven until chicken is tender and rice is done, about 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange fluff
directions: You can use strawberry Jell-O and strawberries or lime Jell-O and pineapple together.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pretty bowl.
Chill.

title: repta denton's southern spoonbread
directions: Let milk come to a boil and put in sugar, butter and salt. Stir in 1/2 cup meal and the well beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the mixture.
Pour in buttered baking dish or pan and cook at 375° for 1 hour.

title: apple blossom cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Slightly beat eggs; then add with oil to dry mix.
Don't mix thoroughly; leave some dry.
Then fold in pecans and pie filling.
Do not overmix.
Leave some dry, this makes crunchy topping.
Bake 1 hour or until done at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: seafoam punch
directions: Place soft drink powder, sugar and milk in a large punch bowl. Stir to dissolve.
Spoon in vanilla ice cream by small spoonfuls. Carefully pour in lemon-lime drink.
Serve immediately.
Makes 15 servings.

title: beans n' corn
directions: Wash and cut string beans in tiny round pieces (to resemble corn).
Boil in salted water for 15 minutes.
Saute in butter, onions and tops.
Add corn and seasonings.
Cook for 15 minutes. Strain water from beans and add corn mixture.
Steam 10 minutes to let seasonings penetrate.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: heavenly rice
directions: In large pan, put rice, water and margarine.
Stir only once. Put lid on pan; bring to a boil.
Turn heat down, but continue to boil 25 minutes.
Do not stir.
Remove lid; add sugar, marshmallows, pineapple and sliced cherries.
Put lid on for 5 minutes to melt marshmallows, then stir.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water.
Saute green pepper and onion in small amount of butter until both are tender.
Alternate layers in medium-size casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook onion and garlic until soft.
Add ground beef and cook until done. Add spices, tomato sauce and water.
Layer in a 9 or 10-inch round ovenproof baking dish the flour tortillas, sauce and cheese 2 times.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done and bubbly.

title: chimis
directions: Cook your roast in the crock-pot all day (approximately 8 hours). Put enough water to cover about 1-inch over the roast. You can add salt, pepper, onion salt and garlic salt if you like but it is not necessary. When the roast is done, remove all fat and pull the meat apart into shreds. Chop your onion and garlic very fine. Heat about 2 to 3 tablespoons of oil in frying pan and saute your onion and garlic for about 3 to 5 minutes. Add your diced chiles and then add your meat. Mix well and then add about 3/4 cup of water, 2 teaspoons chili powder, 1/8 teaspoon garlic powder, 1/8 teaspoon onion powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Mix well and simmer, covered, for about 30 minutes, stirring frequently. Warm tortillas in microwave enough to soften. Spoon meat mixture onto tortilla (be sure to drain juice of they will get soggy) and sprinkle a lot of cheese onto meat and then roll up like a burrito. Do this until all the meat is gone. Serve with salsa, sour cream and gucamole.

title: macaroni and cheese italian style
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 3 to 4-quart shallow baking dish.
In a heavy saucepan, melt butter over moderately low heat. Add flour.
Whisk for 3 minutes.
Add milk and reserved tomato juice in a a stream, whisking to keep smooth.
Bring to a boil, whisking.
Chop in tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Simmer until thickened, 3 minutes.

title: frozen corn
directions: Husk corn and cut off cobs.
Measure 12 cups into a large kettle. Add rest of ingredients.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Cool. Place in freezer bags and freeze.

title: beer batter fried fish
directions: Dip fish in batter and fry in skillet until done on both sides.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased dish and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Blend shortening into dry ingredients; add egg (lightly beaten) and almond flavoring.
Chill; roll into balls and dip tops in sugar.
Place on baking sheet; flatten slightly and press almonds in centers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll biscuit pieces in cinnamon sugar, place in bundt pan. Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts over biscuit pieces. Melt margarine and brown sugar together and pour over biscuits. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: baklava
directions: Mix nuts, zwieback, cinnamon, cloves and sugar.
Butter 13 x 10-inch pan.
Place 1 sheet of filo dough in pan and then butter sheet with pastry brush.
Continue until you have 7 to 8 sheets layered.
Spread nut mixture evenly over layered dough, then continue to cover mixture with 1 sheet of filo dough at a time, buttering each sheet as it is placed on top.
Continue until all pastry sheets are used.
Cut into serving pieces.
Pour remaining melted butter over pastry.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Pour syrup over baklava while hot.
Let cool before serving.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cook bell peppers in salt water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain. Cook beef in skillet with onions and garlic.
Drain.
Put all in a bowl and mix:
corn, rice, tomato sauce, pepper and salt.
Stuff bell peppers.
Cook in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening.
Work in yeast with hands.
Add buttermilk.
Makes a soft dough.
Keeps up to a week in refrigerator.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in one cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Add small can crushed pineapple.
Slightly thicken preceding mixture.
Mix whipped cream and cream cheese; add to jello mixture.
Serves 6.

title: georgia peach pie
directions: Roll half of pastry; fit into a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine sugar, tapioca and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add peaches and toss gently to coat.
Sprinkle on almond extract and stir.
Pour peach mixture into pastry shell; dot with butter.
Roll remaining pastry and place over filling.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and bake an additional 40 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix ingredients and press in oblong pan.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar.
Pour on top of dish and bake until browned in 400° oven.

title: stuffed mushrooms(makes 30 appetizers)
directions: Remove mushroom stems.
Chop enough stems to make 1/2 cup. Cook mushroom caps in margarine for 5 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and Parmesan cheese until well blended.
Add chopped stems and onion.
Mix well and fill caps.
Broil until golden in color.

title: biscuits
directions: Beat and
drop in greased and floured muffin pan.
Bake at 450°.

title: cindy's red hot chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion in a large stock pot.
Drain and return to stock pot.
Add spices and remainder of ingredients. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour on low setting.
Thicken with flour or cornstarch or thin with tomato juice.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel the potatoes and put in cold water. Wipe each potato and grate fine or blend in blender until coarse. There should be no pieces. Grate or blend coarsely the onion also. Mix with potatoes. Drain some of the liquid in the potatoes. Add about 2 tablespoons flour and the salt and pepper.
Mix egg and stir into the potato mixture.
Heat skillet and shortening.
When skillet is hot, spoon in a tablespoon of potato mixture and flatten.
Brown on one side, turn over and brown the other side. Serve with sour cream or applesauce.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and divide into gallon jugs.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Combine gelatin, jello, sugar and water.
Mix until jello and sugar have dissolved.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into mold; chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf with mayonnaise.

title: "sugar free" raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins oil, water and spices for 3 minutes. Cool. Dissolve salt, soda, sweetner and water together. Add eggs, flour, baking powder, nuts and cool raisins mixture, drop by tsp. on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 375 degrees for 10 minutes. These need to refrigerated. Freeze well.

title: apple salad
directions: Core apples; do not peel.
Slice.
Combine apples, celery, pecans, pineapple and cheese.
Mix together mayonnaise and sour cream; add to apple mixture.
Toss to coat evenly.
Serve chilled.

title: blueberry crumb pie
directions: Mix together and pat in pie pan.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream shortening until soft; gradually add sugar, creaming after each addition until mixture is fluffy.
Beat in the egg, then add molasses.
Measure flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt into sifter.
Sift dry ingredients over creamed mixture and blend well.

title: swedish unbaked cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together thoroughly.
Form into balls; roll in granulated sugar and chill before serving.

title: soft peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl combine raisins, dates, banana, peanut butter, water, egg whites and vanilla; beat until blended.
Add oatmeal, flour and baking soda.
Mix to blend thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto nonstick baking sheet. Bake about 10 minutes until browned on underside.
Cool on rack, then store in airtight container.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on a large plate; cover with Hormel chili and top with shredded cheese.
Microwave for 3 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: cranberry apple relish
directions: In food grinder, using medium-coarse blade, grind all fruits. Add sugar and mix well.

title: bell pepper casserole
directions: Melt oleo; cube pepper and onion.
Saute in oleo.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until slightly firm.

title: turkey meatball stroganoff(low-fat)
directions: Combine turkey, crushed croutons and garlic powder.
Form into balls.
Spray large skillet with nonfat cooking spray.
Brown turkey balls on all sides.
Remove and drain on paper towels to remove the fat.
In the same skillet, cook the onions until tender in 2 tablespoons liquid Butter Buds (if needed).
There might be enough moisture left in the pan from the turkey.
Add the mushrooms and flour; stir in the broth and water.
Boil.
Return the turkey balls to the skillet; heat, but do not boil.
Simmer, uncovered, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in yogurt, but do not boil.
Serve turkey balls and sauce over cooked linguine.
Serves 6.

title: chili egg puff
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until light and lemon colored. Add flour, salt, baking powder, Jack cheese and melted butter; blend smoothly.
Stir in chilies and cottage cheese.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Center appears firm.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over TVP and ketchup.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Saute onion, pepper and garlic.
Add TVP along with the spices.
Add tomatoes and beans.
Cover and simmer 30 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: In blender, crush ice finely.
Add banana, honey, yogurt and fruit and blend until smooth.
I usually use the same flavor yogurt as fruit.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix 2 cups bran cereal and boiling water. Set aside.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: diabetic raisin cookies
directions: In a saucepan, boil raisins, water, sweetener, spices and oleo for 3 minutes. Cool. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 9-10 minutes.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix yeast, warm water, flour and salt.
Let rise for about 15 minutes.
Roll; shape (about size of pencil) 12-inches long.
Dip completely in cold water soda solution.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: impossible french apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 10-inch pie pan.
Mix apples and spices together.
Turn into pie pan.
Beat remaining ingredients, except Streusel, until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with mixer.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle with Streusel. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix together and beat well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased Bundt pan.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out on rack.
When completely cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
This is a moist cake.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine and boil all ingredients except eggs and garlic. Simmer for a few minutes.
Place eggs in bowl or jar.
Strain mixture over eggs.
Add garlic.
Place in refrigerator for 3 days (or longer).
Drain and dry to eat.

title: smoked salmon log
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Thoroughly mix with salmon.
Add next 3 ingredients; add onion salt and pepper.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
The next morning, roll into a log. Roll log in finely chopped pecans to which chopped parsley has been added.
Serves 20.
Can be frozen.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt oleo and cheese.
Mix flour and milk.
Add to cheese and oleo mixture.
Clean broccoli and cut into small pieces and add to mixture of cheese, oleo and milk.
Cook to boil.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool to room temperature.
Add pudding to milk in bowl; beat with whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Quickly pour in jello; stir with wire whisk until blended.
Pour at once into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo in a large boiler. Add sliced squash, onion, salt and pepper. Cook until tender on low heat until liquid has cooked low.
Add mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle rest of French fried onions on top and bake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender; drain and mash. Add all ingredients except 1/2 stick of butter and 1/2 cup of crumbs to squash.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle the remaining crumbs on top.
Pour remaining melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about one hour or until brown on top. Serves 8.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pecans.
After mixing, stir in pecans.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli flowerets in water until tender.
Drain.
Open chicken and cheese soups and add 2 cans of water.
Put in large boiler.
Add broccoli to soup mixture.
Thin with milk if too thick.
Serve hot, topped with cheese.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Mix ingredients (except Tony's seasoning), including liquid from beans.
Cook in a slow cooker for 4 or 5 hours.
Tony's Creole seasoning may be added just before serving.
Serves 20 to 24 when served over rice with French bread and a green salad.

title: lemon chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter together.
Press into bottom and side of pan (9 x 12-inch).
Then mix cream cheese, 1 egg, confectioners sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over mixture. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In large skillet, heat oil, garlic and Mexican seasonings over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; saute until tender, about 4 minutes.
Add red pepper, onion and lime juice; saute 4 minutes. Spoon mixture on pita or taco shell.
If desired, top with salsa or sour cream; or lettuce and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: krispie m&m's bars
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup in 2-quart saucepan until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in crisp rice cereal.
Stir to blend.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and crumble.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and onion to fat in skillet. Add crumbled bacon.
Heat thoroughly.
Add cabbage and parsley.
Cook until tender.

title: dressing for baked turkey or chicken
directions: Cook celery and onion in a small amount of water until tender (about 10 minutes).
Drain.
In a large mixing bowl combine biscuits, celery, onion and beaten eggs.
Add stuffing mix and other dry ingredients.
Mix in approximately 2 quarts stock until right consistency.
Grease baking pan with margarine.
Bake at 300° to 325° for about 45 to 60 minutes until dressing is firm and brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup, celery, onion, nuts, rice and seasonings.
Blend well.
Stir in lemon juice, mayonnaise and water.
Chop eggs.
Add to mixture.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400° until bubbly.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Garnish with egg slices that remain.
Serves 4.

title: red meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into a mold except the sauce. Cover mold with any spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of sugar over sauce to remove acid.
Cover at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste.

title: angel food cake
directions: Combine egg whites, cold water and salt. Whip until foamy. Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff but not hard. Mix sugar, flour, vanilla and almond extract together. Fold in egg whites. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Invert pan to cool.

title: stuffed mushrooms marsala
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, mushroom stalks and garlic in butter until onion is transparent.
Fry bacon until crisp.

In a mixing bowl, combine sauteed vegetables, crumbled bacon and bread crumbs. Mix into a firm paste, adding small amounts of water as necessary. Fill mushroom caps with mixture and place them in a baking dish just large enough to hold all of them.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Slice peppers in half (lengthwise) and hollow out.
Precook green pepper ahead about 2 minutes before putting meat mixture. Combine 1/2 of the tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Fill each half pepper.
Place stuffed pepper in 2-quart dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over the top of the peppers.
Cook on High in microwave for 15 minutes, turning dish every 5 minutes (you can precook onion and add into the meat mixture).
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate caramel cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mixes as directed.
Cool.
Cut tops off of layers to level.
Place first cake layer on cake plate smooth side down.
Pour part of caramel topping over cake and allow to soak in.
Spoon layer of filling over this layer.
Place second cake layer atop filling smooth side down and repeat caramel and filling layers.
Place third layer smooth side up and frost with icing.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: * Use egg whites for the meringue.

title: striped jello salad(can be used for dessert)
directions: Each package of jello will be made with 3/4 cup boiling water and 3/4 cup cold water.
There will be four jello layers with filling between each jello layer.
It is time consuming, but the end result is worth it.

title: shrimp or crabmeat dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, pimento and green onions.
Arrange this into a ring and place shrimp or crabmeat on top of ring.
Top with shrimp sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: rabbit barbecue
directions: Cook rabbit until well done.
Take off bone and chop up. Combine all other ingredients.
Bring to boil and add rabbit meat. Simmer until about dry.

title: country white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt, eggs, oil and 3 c flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6-8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning dough once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down. Divide in half and shape into loaves.
Place in 2 greased 9 X 5 X 3 inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans to cool on wire racks.

title: broccoli chicken
directions: Cook chicken, in buttered skillet, over medium heat, approximately 10 minutes.
Stir in soup, water and pepper.
Heat to a boil.
Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until broccoli is done.
Stir occasionally.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Mix bananas and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to banana mixture. Add milk and vinegar.
Add oil, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes in a greased and floured bread pan.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mash cream cheese with a fork.
Grate cucumber on medium size grater.
Combine cream cheese, cucumber, onion, mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.
Makes enough spread for 1 large size loaf of bread (22 slices).
Prepare and cut into fourths.

title: scalloped turkey
directions: Cook celery and green pepper in 1 tablespoon butter.
Remove mixture from pan.
Melt remaining butter in pan.
Blend in flour and salt.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add turkey, celery, green pepper and pimento.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts. Chill 1 hour. Form into ball, then roll in pecans.

title: melon ball delight
directions: Prepare gelatin in according to package directions.
Chill until partially set.
Add melon balls.
Chill until firm.
May be served with cottage cheese or low-calorie dressing.

title: cowpoke beans
directions: Cover beans with water and bring to boil and let cook 2 minutes.
Turn off heat and let set 1 hour.
Add ham, bacon, onion and garlic.
Again bring to boil, turn down, and simmer until beans are cooked.
Pour off part of juice and reserve.
Add tomatoes and spices and cook for about 1/2 hour longer.
Add some reserved juice to keep beans from sticking.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and let stand 2 hours, then drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, then add squash mixture and boil 5 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Makes 10 pints.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce raisin bread(1 loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix first 11 ingredients together, adding raisins last.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts (optional). Sprinkle on top before baking.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Freezes well.

title: crunchy cheese dip
directions: Drain the pineapple, reserving 1 tablespoon juice.
In a small bowl, combine pineapple, cream cheese, water chestnuts, chives, salt, pepper, and pecans.
Stir in reserved juice and mix well.
Garnish with parsley.
Cover and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray pan with Pam spray.
Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend 1 minute.
Pour in pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until crust puffs up.
Serves 6.

title: best blueberry muffins
directions: Rinse blueberries.
Remove 1/2 cup.
Dry remaining berries. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs singly, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Crush the 1/2 cup blueberries with a fork and mix into batter.
Add remaining berries and mix by hand.
Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until nicely browned.
Cool 30 minutes before removing from pans.
Store, uncovered.
Makes about 16 muffins.

title: egg bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Add more milk, if needed.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Mix well and line a 13 x 9-inch pan with this mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 300° for cool.
Combine 2 sticks of butter, powdered sugar and eggs. Beat until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Spread this over the cooled crust.
Place bananas on top of cream mixture.
Place the pineapple over that.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with cherries and nuts.
Chill and cut into small squares.

title: south carolina cobbler
directions: In a bowl, gently toss peaches, 1 cup of sugar and almond extract; set aside.
Pour margarine into a 2-quart baking dish. In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt and remaining sugar; stir in milk.
Mix well.
Pour evenly over margarine (do not stir).
Top with peach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: white christmas pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix together in saucepan sugar, flour, salt and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Stir in gradually 1 1/2 cup milk; cook over low heat, stirring until it boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in softened gelatin.
Cool.
When partially set, beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Blend in vanilla and almond extract.
Gently fold in whipping cream; carefully fold into a meringue of egg whites, sugar and cream of tartar.
Fold in 1 cup of moist shredded coconut.
Put into a baked pie shell; sprinkle with coconut.
Chill until set.
Take out 20 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In mixer, cream butter; add sugar, eggs and spice.
Mix in oatmeal, flour, baking powder and milk.
Drop by teaspoon on greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: artichoke hors d'oeuvres
directions: Use oil from 1 jar of artichokes to saute onion and garlic. Beat eggs.
Add artichokes and other ingredients.
Place in 9-inch square pan and bake for 30 minutes in 325° oven or until done. Cut in squares.
Freezes well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package (but only to separate; do not overcook).
Drain and place in greased casserole dish.
Mix mayonnaise, beaten egg, soup, Cheddar cheese, onion, crackers, salt and pepper.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: gooey cheesecake
directions: Mix well and spread into bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of greased 9 x 13 pan.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted butter; put 1/3 of crumbs in shallow baking dish. Pour 1 can oysters with juice over crumbs; add pepper. Repeat layers, with crumbs on top. Add milk; set 15 minutes. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown on top. Serve hot.

title: granny minnie's peanut candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into dish.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: *pat meiklejohn's chicken casserole
directions: Cover bottom of buttered casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch or larger) with the onion slices.
Dip pieces of chicken in melted butter and set aside.
Cover layer of onions with rice, then layer of chicken on rice.
Sprinkle with marjoram flakes.
Mix soup and water and spoon over chicken.
Seal with aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours or at 250° for 3 hours and 15 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown together lightly: hamburger, bacon and onion.
Mix together rest of ingredients, then mix all with meat mixture in crock-pot.
Cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours or put in greased casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: boiled raisin cookies
directions: Boil the raisins in 1 c. water for 5 min.
Add baking soda when cool.
Mix the brown sugar, butter and eggs.
Stir in the salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in the raisins and water.
Mix the flour with the baking powder and stir into the raisin mixture.
Add the chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by tsp. on greased cookie sheet. Bake 325 for 10-12 min.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: ronald reagan's macaroni and cheese
directions: Stir butter and egg into macaroni.
Mix salt and mustard with 1 tablespoon hot water and add to milk.
Add 2 1/2 cups cheese to macaroni.
Pour macaroni and cheese into a buttered casserole. Add milk.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until custard is set and top is crusty.

title: "my grandmother's banana bread"
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix bananas with sour milk.
Alternately add bananas and dry ingredients to batter.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased Bundt or long loaf pan for about 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon cakes(serves 6)
directions: Drain salmon.
Reserve liquid (set aside).
Remove skin; flake salmon with fork and set aside.
Combine cracker crumbs and reserved liquid.
Let stand 5 minutes (or until liquid is absorbed); stir in salmon, cornmeal and next 3 ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Fry in hot oil on medium heat until brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Cut chicken into nugget size pieces.
Melt butter in shallow dish.
Combine bread crumbs, parmesan cheese, garlic, salt and parsley flakes.
Dip chicken into butter, roll in crumb mixture. Arrange in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour.

title: date-rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Set aside.
Heat milk in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling, water or in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Beat eggs lightly in bowl; add honey, vanilla, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and salt.
Slowly stir egg mixture into hot milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 15 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rice and dates.
Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining nutmeg.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until custard is set. Makes 4 servings.

title: karo icing
directions: Mix Karo, sugar, water & vanilla in a double boiler. Bring to boil for about 5 minutes.
Add to beaten egg whites and beat until fluffy.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Sprinkle rice in a 9 x 12-inch pan (glass).
Mix cream of mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup with 1 can water.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken parts over rice.
Sprinkle on envelope of dry onion soup mix over this and a little paprika.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: indian curried chicken and broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put chicken or turkey in a shallow baking dish, cover with foil and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until meat is tender and no longer pink.
Combine yogurt and flour; set aside.
Stir water, curry powder, garlic, salt, lemon peel and paprika together in saucepan and bring to boiling.
Reduce the heat, cover and simmer for 1 minute.
Add yogurt mixture.
Cook until mixture is thickened and bubbly; continue cooking for 1 more minute.
Arrange broccoli on a serving platter; place poultry on top.
Pour sauce over poultry and top with peanuts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Combine cabbage, salt and water in a 3-quart glass casserole; cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Cook in microwave oven 10 to 12 minutes on High or until crisp-tender.
Stir once.
Add a mixture of vinegar and sugar to crisp-tender cabbage.
Mix well. Cook, covered, in microwave oven 1 to 2 minutes on High or until tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add dry ingredients alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325°
for
hours
in greased and floured tube pan.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into refrigerator tray.
Freeze until firm, stirring three times at 30 minutes intervals.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: kraut
directions: Heat to almost boiling.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Then pour over chopped cabbage.
Put in jar to can.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form into 2 balls, then roll in pecans. Chill.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, peanut butter and butter; bring to a boil. Remove and add corn flakes.
Place in cake pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Store in a plastic bag or covered container.

title: barbecued chicken paprika
directions: Quarter, wash and dry chicken.
Place in shallow pan.
Mix together the oil, garlic and paprika.
Pour over chicken and marinate for 3 or 4 hours, turning the chicken every 1/2 hour. Season with salt and pepper just before barbecuing over hot coals, basting frequently with marinade.

title: quick chicken ala king
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Blend in softened cream cheese, mushroom soup and pepper.
Stir in chicken and sliced mushrooms with liquid.
Heat to boiling. Add green pepper and pimento.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: jello mold salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
In same bowl, mix together jello, strawberries with juice, pineapple with juice and bananas. Pour 1/2 of mixture in serving bowl.
Chill until set.
Spread sour cream over top.
Add remaining jello mixture over sour cream. Refrigerate until set.

title: jim's quick tarragon chicken
directions: Saute onions and
garlic in olive oil.	Flatten breasts to 1/2 original
thickness.
Add
butter to sauteed onions and garlic, then add chicken breasts.
Saute to golden brown.
Add mushrooms and continue to saute until tender, then add 3/4 cup wine, tarragon and
salt.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend
arrowroot	into balance of wine and add to chicken.
Stir until
thickened.
Serve
with
rice
or pasta. Serves 4 or 2 Reeves.

title: chicken and tortilla casserole
directions: Blend soup, sour cream, tomatoes, onions and 2 cups cheese. Layer in a casserole dish in the following order: 1/2 of the soup mixture, chicken, tortillas and rest of soup mixture.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: rainbow salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in separate bowls with 1 cup water each.
Add 3/4 cup very cold water to each; set aside.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water in large bowl; set aside.
Add sugar and vanilla to scalded milk; pour into bowl with Knox. Gradually add and stir smooth the sour cream (be careful, or it will curdle).
While the cream mixture cools slightly, begin layering the salad.
If using a large casserole, layer by 1-cup measures.
Let set in refrigerator 15 to 20 minutes for each layer, checking often, until the layer is just hard enough to allow the next to be added.
If using 2 small casseroles, layer by 1/2-cup measures.

title: chicken with sherry
directions: Salt
chicken
to
taste
and
place in casserole dish. Melt butter
and
add sherry wine.
Pour part over chicken and bake at 350°.
Use balance of sauce to baste chicken frequently.
Bake until
golden brown.
Add sliced mushrooms near end of cooking time.

title: burritos
directions: Brown meat. Season with desired seasoning. Stir in spinach and salsa. Warm the tortillas. Spoon 1/4 cup meat (depending on size of tortilla) in center of tortilla. Cover with cheese.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add fresh strawberries. Bake in sheet cake pan at 350°.
Let cake completely cool.

title: mexi-cass
directions: Brown ground chuck, pepper, salt and chili powder.
Set aside. Mix enchilada sauce mix, tomato sauce and water.
Pour over meat. Set
aside.
Layer pinto beans, corn chips, refried beans and corn chips in order given in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Mix together cream cheese and sour cream with garlic powder.
Spread on as next layer.
Pour meat sauce on top of this.
Melt milk and Velveeta in microwave and pour over meat sauce. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: light lemon squares
directions: Mix first four ingredients until crumbly.
Press into the bottom of 8-inch square pan that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Beat egg whites, sugar and zest until smooth.
In small bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the egg mixture and blend.
Mix in the lemon juice.
Pour over hot crust and bake for 20 minutes or until top is light golden brown and set.
Let cool in the pan on a rack. Spray a sharp knife with nonstick cooking spray and cut into squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and pour into ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with cake mix and pecans.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: quick crabby shrimp tray
directions: Place both packages of cream cheese on a serving tray or plate in the center, side by side. Mound crab meat on top of cream cheese. Arrange boiled shrimp around crab mound, tails up. Drizzle cocktail sauce over crab and shrimp. Arrange crackers around edge of tray and serve.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in lime juice and food coloring.
Pour into prepared pastry shell. Bake 8 minutes.
Cool. Chill.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove from broth and bone.
Reserve chicken broth.
Mix together soups and milk.
Grease 2 (2-quart) casserole dishes.
Alternate layers of chicken (broken in small pieces) with soup mixture, leaving soup mixture on top.
Moisten dressing with chicken broth and put on top of soup mixture.
Bake until brown at 350°.
Makes 2 casseroles.
Freeze one for later use.

title: overnight souffle
directions: Put bread cubes in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Beat eggs, milk and spices together and pour on top of cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before baking, crumble bacon on top, then if desired pour melted butter over all.
Place casserole pan into larger pan of warm water.
Cook in 325° oven 1 hour 15 minutes.
Until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: grandma's potato candy
directions: Add vanilla and salt to mashed potatoes.
Chill.
Add confectioners sugar slowly to chilled potatoes until mixture is stiff and dry.
Divide mixture into 3 parts.
Working with one part at a time, roll out to about a 1/4-inch thickness on waxed paper (it should form a rectangle about 4 x 12 inches).
Spread with a thin layer of peanut butter.
Roll up as for jelly roll.
Repeat with remaining potato mixture and peanut butter.
Chill several hours.
Slice (not too thick; this is rich).
Store in refrigerator.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch cake pan, put pineapple. Spread evenly, then add cherries and spread evenly. Add (dry) cake mix.
Add pecans and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Put butter in glass baking dish.
Beat eggs, add flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin nut bars
directions: Cook raisins in water.
Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Then add raisins and raisin water.
Add flour, soda, walnuts, cinnamon and salt and mix well.
Pour on cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top while hot with powdered sugar, milk and butter icing.

title: pickled beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Mix all
together
until
well blended.
Pat out on wax paper, moistened with water.
Spread chopped onion and chopped apricots on meat.
Roll up, making compact roll.
Put in a 9 x 5-inch bread pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: tangy lemon muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and add to creamed mixture.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add lemon extract.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with lemon juice; mix well. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and lemon peel.
Blend thoroughly.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Saute onions, celery and green peppers.
Add to browned hamburger.
Fold in cheese, tomatoes, salt, pepper and spaghetti.
Place in baking dish and pour can of tomato soup on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add
them with hot water; mix well.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan
at
for	20 to 30 minutes.
Will keep in the refrigerator for a week.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Bring all to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes.

title: potato salad for 50
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on. Peel and dice potatoes when done. Add eggs, celery and onion which have been cut fine. Set aside. Mix salad dressing, mustard, sugar, vinegar, milk, salt and pepper. Pour this mixture over diced potatoes. Refrigerate.

title: lite fruit salad supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients in serving bowl, mixing well.
Chill to serving temperature.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: bolo do pico
directions: Bring water and salt to boil.
Add boiling water slowly to corn flour stirring vigorously until smooth.
Cool by stirring occasionally.
This mixture hardens as it cools.
Add regular flour and knead for about 5 minutes.
Make a round ball and roll it on a board with corn flour, making it very smooth.
Flatten dough with the palm of your hand making a smooth round circle about 1/2-inch thick.
Bake in a baking sheet in a preheated 450° to 500° oven for about 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cool on a rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix altogether.
Grease casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mandel bread
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar gradually.
Add flour, salt and baking powder sifted together.
Add oil, nuts and flavoring.
Shape like a loaf of bread, not more than 2 inches wide or 1 inch high, but long (about 3 loaves in all).

title: okra etouffee
directions: Place okra in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish; drizzle with oil. Top with tomatoes and green chiles, onion and bell pepper; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover loosely with aluminum foil. Bake at 400°, stirring occasionally, 1 hour. Stir together potato chips and breadcrumbs; sprinkle over casserole. Bake, uncovered, 15 more minutes or until lightly browned. Serve over rice, if desired. YIELD: 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies(peanut butter)
directions: You will also need wax paper.

title: salad dressing ii
directions: Combine all ingredients and
blend
together
in blender or food processor until blended.
Refrigerates
indefinitely.
This is great on spinach or any fresh green garden salad.

title: butterball cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix cans of corn, eggs, sour cream and corn muffin mix with 1 stick melted oleo.
Grease bowl; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexicali franks
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat until hot. Add frankfurters and saute until browned.
Remove with slotted spoon; place on serving dish and keep warm.
Add onions and garlic to drippings and saute 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and their liquid, beans and their liquid, salsa, rice, chili powder and water. Bring to boil and simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Sprinkle cheese over rice and serve with frankfurters.

title: turkey casserole
directions: This is from my grandmother's book "Domestic Cookery," printed in 1851.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain meat and onions in a large Dutch oven.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer. Cook for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: create "a" cookie
directions: Spread icing slightly thick on top of chocolate chip cookie. Unwrap peanut butter cup and place upside-down in bottom center of cookie.
Arrange 4 to 5 candy corn above peanut butter cup with small ends touching the peanut butter cup.
Draw two beady eyes and a beak on top of peanut butter cup.
Now enjoy the most tasty "turkey" cookie ever.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute onion; beat eggs slightly and melt butter.
Add all ingredients to beef.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: talerine
directions: Saute in oil, onion, garlic and pepper.
When tender add tomatoes; stew 10 minutes.
Fry hamburger in onion grease.
Add to mixture with cayenne pepper.
Add corn, salt, olives, olive brine, ketchup, sugar, oregano and Worcestershire sauce and grated cheese (save some to spread on top).
Drain noodles; add to mixture and put in baking dishes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° about 1/2 hour.
This can be made and frozen to use later.

title: red hots jello salad
directions: Melt the red hots in the boiling water, then add jello.
Cool a little, then add applesauce and pour in bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: one pan broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: my mom's fritto vuoto(empty fritters)
directions: Beat eggs and set aside.
Melt butter in boiling water.
Add salt.
When butter is completely melted, add eggs and flour.
Stir until well blended.
Cool.
Form in balls 1 to 1 1/2-inches.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown. These can be eaten plain or in spaghetti sauce. Delicious!

title: cajun seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Place in an airtight container.
When boiling a pound of shrimp, season water with 2 tablespoons of mix.
Use 1 tablespoon with 1 pound ground meat.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Add dry ingredients to vinegar and stir.
Add oil slowly and beat with mixer or processor at high speed until desired thickness.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter about 3 minutes or until light and fluffy, then add sugar and continue to beat until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time beating after each.
Sift flour and soda and salt together. Add to creamed mixture with sour cream.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
Bake at 325°.
I grease and flour my pan.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix 1/2 cup soup, beef onion soup mix, bread crumbs and egg.
Firmly shape mixture into a 4 x 8-inch loaf and place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: kid's silly putty
directions: Combine equal parts of liquid glue and liquid starch.
Mix with hands, works best when kept warm.
Store in 2-ounce Tupperware Midgets.

title: honey glazed snack mix
directions: Combine cereal, pretzels and pecans, set aside.
Melt butter in small saucepan; stir in honey and blend well.
Pour over cereal mixture and stir to coat evenly.
Spread evenly on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until mixture is lightly glazed.
Spread on waxed paper to cool completely.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil oil, water and cocoa.
Remove from heat; cool a little.
Add eggs, sugar, salt, soda and vanilla.
Mix real well. Add flour and beat real well.
Mix in sour cream last, by hand. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: my favorite pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Line 2 (14-inch) pizza pans with dough. Drizzle each dough with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Set aside 24 slices of the pepperoni to be used later. Sprinkle the remaining pepperoni slices over the 2 doughs. Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over both doughs. Combine tomato sauce, oregano, anise seed and garlic; pour half of mixture on each pie, spreading evenly. Grate Mozzarella cheese and put half on each pie. Put rest of Parmesan cheese over both pies. Drizzle each pie with 1 tablespoon olive oil and trim edges with pepperoni slices you set aside. Bake 25 minutes or until crust is browned and filling is bubbling well. Serve hot.

title: sausage onion treats
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook the sausage with the onion; drain.
Mix the Bisquick with 1 egg and the milk.
Put in bottom of baking pan.
Sprinkle on caraway seed.
Spoon the sausage mixture over the top.
Mix the sour cream with 1 egg and a dash of salt; spoon over top of sausage-onion mixture and spread to cover the top.
Top with paprika.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Mmmmm, good.

title: crisp pie crust
directions: Blend flour, Crisco and salt until crumbly.
Beat egg, vinegar and water.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Stores well in freezer.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix sauce and jelly.
Bake, covered, browned meatballs at 300° for one hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs until thick; add corn and set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and pepper; slowly stir in milk.
Combine with corn mixture; blend well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake in a moderately slow (325°) oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: ginger ale-sherbet punch
directions: Beat together 1 quart of ginger ale and 1 pint of sherbet. Continue adding ginger ale and sherbet as needed.
Yields fifty 1/2-cup servings.

title: floys' chili
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add ground beef and onion and cook until done.
Color of meat should turn from red to gray.
Add tomato sauce with just enough water to cover the meat well.
Then add all spices and stir well.
Cook at a slow simmer for one hour. Makes a medium paste with cornmeal and water.
Add to mixture. Stir well often and simmer slowly for thirty minutes.
Pour in 1-pound aluminum loaf pans and freeze for later.

title: papprkakar (swedish gingersnaps)
directions: Combine Karo and sugar.
Let come to a boil.
Remove from fire and add butter while hot.
Add cream.
Sift flour and spices together.
Add to the first mixture.
Mix the night before and bake in the a.m. Roll very thin and cut with cookie cutter.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften and mix together.
Spread on bottom of serving plate. Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, grated sharp Cheddar cheese and chopped black olives.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place butter, sugar and evaporated milk in a saucepan under medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from stove and mix in thoroughly the peanut butter, marshmallow and vanilla.
Pour into 2 oblong greased brownie pans.
Score when cool.
Very important, do not stop stirring fudge while it is being cooked.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Mix soup with water.
Spread small amount in bottom of casserole dish.
Prepare stuffing.
Spread about 1/4 cup stuffing on each slice of turkey breast and roll up.
Place side by side in casserole.
Top with remaining soup.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave at Full power for 12 minutes, rotating dish after 6 minutes.
"May also bake in oven at 400° for about 30 minutes."

title: sweetheart candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it forms a
hard (clinking) ball when dropped in a cup of cold water.
Add to egg white (well beaten) slowly and beat until ready to pour.
Pour on greased pan.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream the shortening with sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and about 1/2 cup of raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on greased pan.

title: almond crescent rolls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Beat in egg yolk.
Add almonds.
Spread each triangle of dough with almond mixture.
Roll up and bake according to package directions for crescent rolls.

title: van's green beans
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar and Miracle Whip and let stand while you heat beans in their juices until hot, then drain off all juice.
Mix in chopped onions and bacon pieces.
Pour sugar, vinegar and Miracle Whip mixture over beans and stir well.
Heat beans until hot and serve.

title: yogurt
directions: Microwave Cooking:
Place milk in a 1-quart casserole. Microwave on High (100%) for 5 to 6 minutes or to an internal temperature of 180°.
Allow milk to cool in refrigerator for 30 to 35 minutes or until the internal temperature drops to 106° to 110°.

title: orange snack cake
directions: Bake at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
In one bowl combine oats and boiling water.
Set aside.
In a second bowl mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside. In a large bowl cream together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg whites, orange juice and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture alternating with oats, beginning and ending with flour.
Pour into greased pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Take cake out of oven and preheat broiler.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Bring to a boil brown sugar and margarine.
Boil for 2 minutes. Then stir in ground pecans and vanilla.
Break 24 graham crackers in half.
Take the 48 halves and place in rows on a cookie sheet. Pour boiled mixture over graham crackers.
Put in oven and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Take off cookie sheet immediately and cool.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, 3/4 cup butter and 1/2 cup milk together. Spread 1/2 cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 7 minutes at 350°.

title: ultimate 7-layer dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning mix.
Spread onto bottom of 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Layer remaining ingredients over bean mixture; cover.
Refrigerate several hours or until chilled. Serve with tortilla chips or assorted crackers.

title: california blend casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then top with remaining half of the fried onions and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Cook cake as directed.
Punch holes in cake with a wooden spoon.
When cool, mix milk and caramel and pour over top.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed candy bars.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour together. Beat eggs slightly; add to flour mixture. Add milk, vanilla and butter or margarine. Stir until thickened. Pour into baked pie shell.
Add whipped cream.

title: bologna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; store in refrigerator.
Will keep for about 5 days.
Makes 3 cups.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Cut
squash in half.
Scoop seeds and slice in 1/2 inch slices.
Cut
zucchini in rounds, 1/4 inch.
Wash broccoli and slice
stem
1/4 inch and separate flowerets.
Break stem from mushrooms
and
wash.
Slice celery in 1/4-inch slices.
Slice onion in
inch rounds.
Thaw snow peas.
Put olive oil in wok or
electric frying pan.
Add all other vegetables.
Stir and toss
constantly until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Just before serving, sprinkle bouillon granules over vegetables and add water. Stir
well.
Turn off heat.
Cut lemon in half and squeeze
juice over
contents
of
wok.
Toss
well and serve garnished with tomato wedges.

title: christmas cranberries relish
directions: Wash cranberries in cold water.
In an old fashioned hand grinder (use a coarse cutting plate) or in a food processor (a coarse chop) grind or chop all berries.
Quarter but do not peel apples and grind into the berries.
Peel and remove seeds from oranges and grind into mixture.
Add banana last, then stir in sugar to taste.
If you wish, you can grind in some grated orange peel for extra tang.

title: dump cake
directions: Into an ungreased pan, dump the crushed pineapple.
On top of the pineapple, dump the pie filling.
On top of the pie filling, dump the dry cake mix and pecans.
Over the whole thing, pour the melted butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour. Serve warm with a dab of Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: baked crabmeat and shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Sprinkle rice in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups with milk and pour over rice.
Stir.
Lay chicken on the rice and sprinkle with onion soup mix on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 2 hours and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: frozen vegetables
directions: Cook, drain and cool mixed vegetables.
Mix in kidney beans, celery, green pepper and onion.
In small saucepan mix sugar, flour, mustard and vinegar and water mixture.
Cook until thick. Allow to cool and add to vegetable mixture.

title: molasses pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add molasses and butter.
Combine sugar, spices, salt, flour and cornstarch.
Add to first mixture. Mix thoroughly.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into pastry lined pie crust.
Bake in hot oven (425°) about 15 minutes.
Cover pie with pecans, sprinkle with sugar and continue baking for 15 minutes.

title: an indian (apache) chili from new mexico
directions: Dump all ingredients into large pot, including liquid from beans.
Add 1/8 to 1/4 teaspoon chili powder (cayenne only!).
Add a bit of cornmeal to thicken and give the spirit of Mother Earth.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add and mix well oatmeal, coconut, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Roll into the size of large walnuts and flatten on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 1/2 dozen.

title: meatballs and rice
directions: Chop fine the first 3 ingredients.
Mix 1/4 of this with meat, rice, eggs, seasonings and cream.
Shape into balls.
Roll lightly in flour and a bit of paprika.
Fry to copper color; add remaining onions to drippings.
Cook until lightly brown.
Add tomatoes and water.
Simmer slowly for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add parsley and shallots.
Cook about 10 more minutes.

title: diana's easy banana muffins
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Beat salad dressing with bananas.
Stir
all together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 18 muffins.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine milk and marshmallows in heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring often, until marshmallows melt.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold liqueurs and whipped cream into marshmallow mixture. Spoon into pie shell. Garnish with chocolate wafer crumbs (optional). Freeze 4 to 6 hours.

title: apple fritters
directions: Cut apples into small chunks.
Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Beat egg yolks and milk together and add to dry ingredients.
Add apples.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into flour mixture.
Drop tablespoons of batter into hot oil and cook until golden on both sides.
Serve hot, sprinkled with cinnamon-sugar.

title: gooseberry salad
directions: When gelatin starts to harden, add berries, chopped orange and celery.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Crush 1/2 cup Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top of the broccoli mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and chill overnight.
Makes a lot of dip. Serve with fresh vegetables or even small breads or bread sticks.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat.
Spoon off fat.
