Add garlic, parsley flakes, oregano, basil, salt, canned tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Drain and rinse.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, parsley flakes, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Place 1/2 noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Spread 1/2 cottage cheese mix, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat. Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark and add peanut butter, Rice Krispies, marshmallows and peanuts.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Line greased 9 x 13-inch pan with marshmallows.
Pour in cake batter.
Mix Jell-O and strawberries together and pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Strawberries go to bottom and
marshmallows to the top.

title: easy cheese omelet
directions: Have water in bottom of double boiler hot, but not boiling hard.
Mix ingredients well and place in top of double boiler. Cover and leave for exactly 20 minutes without lifting lid.
Serve immediately.
Serves 3 to 4.
Simply delicious!

title: grandma mcelroy's plum pudding
directions: Mix well together.
Put in covered mold.
Set in pot of boiling water just over halfway full.
Keep adding water as it boils away.
Steam for 4 hours.
Add brandy the day you serve pudding or a little at any time you think of it.
Refrigerate. Pudding keeps for two months.
Serve hot topped with hard sauce. Makes 2 (1 pound) molds.
Serves 20.

title: bachelor beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in tightly covered heavy 5-quart pot. Bake in 300° oven for 5 hours.
Do not open oven at any time.
Do not increase amounts of ingredients.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in microwavable large bowl.
Blend or mix thoroughly.
Pour milk over this mixture.
Put butter in pads, over this; do not mix these all together.
Cook (in large microwavable bowl) 2 minutes, until butter is completely soft and melting. Remove from oven; add vanilla and nuts.
Beat mixture until thoroughly combined.
This should be done as quickly as possible after cooking is complete.
Place in greased 2-quart oblong dish. Chill about 1 hour to harden.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve and enjoy!

title: hamburger-rice hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Mix in carrots and potatoes with hamburger.
Mix soups, water and brown sugar together.
Add soup mixture and rice to the hamburger.
Bake 1 to 2 hours at 350°. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hershey chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time. Add flour alternately with Hershey's syrup.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain most of liquid from potatoes and mash in bowl; add applesauce and brown sugar and blend well.
Spray nonstick cooking spray on bottom and sides of casserole.

Spread 1/2 sweet potato mixture on the bottom; layer pie filling over potatoes and sprinkle with nutmeg, then layer the rest of sweet potatoes. Cover with graham cracker crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until it is hot and bubbly and top is slightly brown, 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: chinese salad
directions: Combine cabbage and onions and refrigerate.
Break noodles into small pieces.
In skillet, lightly brown noodles, almonds and sesame seed in butter.
Set aside.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together. Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Boil vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed for 1 minute.
Cool.
Chop cabbage.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out all excess liquid.
Add celery, green pepper, carrot and red mango to cabbage.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture.
Pack in containers and freeze or refrigerate.

title: granny hitchcock's tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop batter in small amounts onto a
greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all together and spoon into hot oil.
Fry until brown. Very yummie.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Let stand 1 hour on each side in mixture.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl. Mix lightly with two forks. Beat together remaining ingredients. Pour over rice. Toss again lightly. Chill. Serve very cold. Can also use canned tomatoes instead of fresh.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple. Stir in all other ingredients and chill. Also a quick dessert.

title: pistachio cream pie
directions: In a bowl, mix by hand dry pudding mix and drained pineapple. This will be a green paste.
Gently fold in Cool Whip.
Place in graham cracker shell and refrigerate.

title: crazy spice cake
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients into ungreased 8 x 8-inch square pan. Make 3 holes in flour mixture.
Place oil in one hole, place vinegar in 2nd hole; pour almond extract in 3rd hole.
Pour water over all and mix with fork until blended.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place 4 cups zucchini in saucepan in cold water. Bring to boil, then drain well (don't cook). Mix all ingredients together except crackers. Pour into greased casserole dish, last cracker crumbs. Pour melted butter over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed pizza
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown sausage and hamburger and drain.
Mix Bisquick and water; divide dough in 2 parts, one larger.
Roll larger section into rectangle and place in pan. Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese, 3/4 cup pizza sauce, meat and other toppings.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Roll remaining dough and place on top of mixture.
Press edges together and make slits in top.
Spread with remaining pizza sauce and cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Drain most of juice off fruit.
Mix everything together and let stand overnight.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make sauce with milk, flour and butter.
Layer with potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice.
After cool, fold in Cool Whip, nuts and buttermilk last.
Chill good.

title: homemade irish cream
directions: Process all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Will keep in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.
Stir before serving.
(I usually double this recipe when serving guests.)

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Cool.
Cut cheese, salami and pepperoni in bite-size pieces.
Slice olives.
Dice pepper, celery and onion.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, oil and vinegar.
Combine the dressing with other ingredients, except tomatoes; chill overnight.
Add tomatoes just before serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer on low heat about 20 minutes until thoroughly mixed.
Stir occasionally.

title: chili - the thickest
directions: Using slow cooker or crock-pot, add all cans of ingredients on high.
Brown together the ground beef, green pepper, onion, garlic, salt, pepper and chili seasoning, then add to canned ingredients. Heat through and serve.
Great with shredded Cheddar cheese on top.

title: lemon lime sheet cake
directions: Other flavors of Jell-O and cakes may be used.
White cake with strawberry Jell-O is good.

title: tropical jello salad
directions: Mix jellos, hot water and cold water.
Refrigerate to partially set.
Mix pineapple, marshmallows, bananas and lemon juice.
Add to jello mixture; refrigerate to set.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Whisk ingredients together until smooth and creamy.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.
Refrigerate until needed.
Serve over tossed salad greens.

title: chicken creame de spinach
directions: Place chicken breasts in foiled pan; cover with seasoning, garlic powder and tomato sauce.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cook egg noodles; drain and cook packed cream spinach.
Mix egg noodles and spinach together; place on bottom of casserole dish. When chicken is ready, place chicken on top of noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover; heat until cheese is melted.

title: easy pancakes
directions: Place biscuit mix in a bowl; make a well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add to biscuit mix, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup batter onto a moderately hot, lightly greased griddle.
Makes 8 pancakes.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Soak grape leaves in warm water for 10 minutes to soften. Combine remaining ingredients (except lemon juice and water) in bowl and mix well.
Take 1 leaf, place shiny side down and fill with 1 teaspoon of meat mix at base of leaf.
Roll into finger shape (firmly).
Place into pan in layers, alternating the direction of each layer.
Add water to cover leaves.
Bring to a boil, then add lemon juice.
Lower heat and simmer for approximately 45 minutes until water is almost completely absorbed.

title: mexican sausage cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Use sheet cake pan sprayed with Pam.

title: "scuse me" bean hotdish
directions: Brown beef, onion, salt and pepper; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook beef until browned; drain.
Mix in the next 5 ingredients; heat to boil.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Add vegetables; cook a few more minutes.
Add to a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread mashed potatoes over top.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until top is set.

title: gail's favorite spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain 1/2 to 1 pound spaghetti. Place in large buttered casserole dish. Gently mix in a large can of whole tomatoes and their sauce chopped up a bit.
Add 1/2 cup tomato juice. Top with 1/2 pound of grated sharp Cheddar cheese. Sprinkle with crumbled crackers and dot with butter. Bake one-half hour at 350° until nice and hot and cheese melted.

title: golden tossies(recipe over 100 years old.)
directions: Blend cream cheese and flour with margarine and form into 48 balls.
Place into miniature muffin tins and press dough into cup shapes with floured fingers.
Divide pecans among shells. Combine eggs, slightly beaten with sugar, melted margarine, vanilla and salt.
Pour over nuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: double boiler pudding
directions: Put brown sugar
in top of double boiler.
Cut buttered bread into cubes
and
spread
over
the sugar.
Sprinkle with raisins. Beat the eggs and add to the milk, salt and vanilla. Pour this mixture
over the bread.
Set over boiling water and keep the water boiling.
Cook about 1 hour.
Do not stir.
The brown sugar makes the sauce.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and/or nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 370°.
Cool completely before serving.

title: tallerina
directions: Cook beef in skillet until brown.
Add bell pepper and onion. Cook until tender.
Add chili powder, tomato and corn.
Cook 15 minutes.
Boil noodles as directed; drain.
Add meat mixture.

title: manhattan meat roll
directions: Brown in heavy pan hamburg, onions and peppers; add other ingredients.
Set aside.
Make a biscuit dough (as light as possible).
Roll out to 1-inch thickness.
Put meat topping on dough roll (like jellyroll) and clip edges together and put on cookie sheet.
Cover with Lipton dry onion soup).
Bake at 350°. Test often.
Cut in slices and cover each piece with gravy.
Serve with baked potato and green vegetable.

title: scotchies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, egg and water.
Beat until creamy.
Add orange extract.
Stir in flour mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add oatmeal and butterscotch chips. Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Bring to boil sugar and syrup.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour over cornflakes.
Mix gently.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Mix and put in refrigerator until congealed.

title: easy mushroom pizza
directions: Drain canned mushrooms; set aside.
Heat 4 tablespoons oil in large skillet.
Add mushrooms and saute for 5 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
In same skillet, heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Add onion and green pepper and saute for 3 minutes.
Combine half of sauce and half of sauteed mushrooms with the onion and pepper in skillet.
Set aside.

title: turnip greens and pot likker
directions: Start salt pork in cold water.
Cook 50 minutes.
Add washed and chopped turnip greens to pork and cook 1 hour.
Cook until water is cooked down.
Season with salt and pepper.
"Dinner for a family."

title: glazed pecans
directions: Mix sour cream and sugar over medium heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until nuts are coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Add egg and molasses. Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture with hot water.
Bake in 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, but the sliced egg.
Put it on top for decoration.
Chill before serving.
Serves 6.

title: apple brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together and set aside.
Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add egg and then flour mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Put in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
I double this and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Yummy.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: eclair roll
directions: Boil water and butter.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and beat with wooden spoon.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each egg is added.
When mixture is smooth, spoon onto a 14-inch pizza pan making a circle.
Bake on middle oven rack for 45 minutes at 400°. When cool, slice on the horizontal.

title: fruit fluff
directions: Mix the cottage cheese, Cool Whip and Jell-O well, then chill. Add favorite fruits.
Example: 1 can pineapple or 1 can mandarin oranges.

title: jigglers
directions: Sprinkle generously with kindness.
Add plenty of faith; mix well.
Spread over a lifetime and serve everybody you meet.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in well.
Sift in flour with salt and baking powder.
Add alternately to batter mix.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: fall apple dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients except last two.
Wash and slice apples; dip in orange juice.
Drain.
Arrange apples in concentric circles on pretty plate and place dip in center in a bowl.
Sprinkle additional chopped peanuts on top of dip. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Fill bottom of saucepan with egg noodles, one layer crumbled by hand to cover bottom.
Add chicken broth and enough water for 2 cups liquid.
Add salt and pepper. Bring to boil and add one cup of rice.
Stir and then cover.
Turn to simmer until water is absorbed, about 20 minutes.

title: apple-nut coffee cake
directions: Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
Toss apples with 2 tablespoons of sugar.
In large bowl, beat butter with 1 1/2 cups sugar until light and fluffy at medium speed.
Add sour cream and remaining ingredients.
Beat at low speed until blended, then at medium speed 1 minute.
Spread batter into 14 x 10-inch greased pan.
Arrange apple slices on top.
Sprinkle with Streusel Topping.

title: layered casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Take off foil and bake for 30 minutes more until done.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix together the sausage, hamburger, eggs, bread crumbs and milk; stuff in noodles.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan; put in manicotti.
Cover with the Italian sauce and cheese.
Cover tightly; bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil together zucchini	and
onions.
Mash zucchini and drain for 3 hours.
Mix
together
cream of chicken soup, sour cream and carrots, then
refrigerate.
Melt
together oleo and stuffing mix. Mix together
zucchini and soup mixture.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer 1/2 stuffing mixture, zucchini mixture and remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake
in
a
350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Call on the phone, then it comes to your door.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix
ground
beef,
egg
and
onion
together (salt and pepper to taste) and shape into balls.
Mix chili sauce, lemon juice
and jelly and heat.
While sauce is heating, brown meat balls
in oven,
approximately 10 minutes on each side.
Drop balls in simmering sauce and cook until tender.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix in order given.
Slice 1 medium onion and add enough cucumbers to fill container covering cucumbers.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in 2 layers.
Split; when cool (4 layers).
Fill and ice with sour cream mixture.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate for 48 hours.

title: apricot pastries
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Sift in flour and salt.
Chill several hours or overnight.
On floured board, roll dough very thin and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place 1/2 teaspoon preserves on each round.
Fold over and seal with fork. Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 375° until firm, but not browned, about 12 minutes.
Sift confectioners sugar over pastries and remove from pan while warm.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in fruit and juice. Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and refrigerate until firm.
Store remaining gelatin at room temperature.
Spoon the sour cream over the congealed gelatin.
Top the sour cream with the remaining gelatin and refrigerate until firm.
Sprinkle the top with pecans.

title: rachel's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add butter, syrup and flour. Blend in pecans, last, then pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will also need 8 clear glasses.

title: rich peanut butter bars
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Melt peanut butter and margarine in bowl over hot water. Add remaining ingredients; stir until blended. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in preheated oven at 350°. Cool; cut into squares.

title: delicious cobbler
directions: Trim crusts from bread and cut each slice into 3 sticks. Place each piece side by side in prepped (greased and floured) 13 x 11-inch pan.
Cover bread with fruit.
(Fresh peaches are delicious.)
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over all. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gallerano's escarole soup
directions: Put beef bone in a pot; cover with water and boil.
After water comes to a boil, add the parsley, onion, potato, carrots and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until the vegetables are a little tender.
Remove the beef bone.
Add the escarole (cut up each leaf 2 times).
Cover and let it cook until tender (add water if needed).
You can add small meatballs.

title: triple cheese strata
directions: Using a 10-inch frying pan, melt one tablespoon butter over medium heat.
Add mushrooms, onion and marjoram and cook until onion begins to turn clear.
Remove from heat.
Spread remaining 2 tablespoons butter over one side of day-old bread.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes leaving crusts on.
Using casserole dish, layer half the bread cubes on the bottom of dish.
Cover with the mushroom-onion mixture.
Combine all three cheeses and dry mustard. Sprinkle over mixture.
Top with remaining bread cubes.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over the bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients 1 to 2 minutes. Pour into 2 large or 6 small lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour.

title: anise cutout cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo.
Add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients. Add to sugar and oleo mixture.
Mix until it forms a stiff dough. Add anise flavoring to mixed dough and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll and cut out on lightly floured board into various shapes.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: raspberry burgundy sauce
directions: Pour wine over berries in a large bowl. Let stand 24 hours at room temperature.
Put mixture in Foley food mill or like device to strain seeds from berries.
Pour strained juice and mashed berries into saucepan.
Add sugar and bring to an almost boil. Freeze for future use.
Excellent over vanilla ice cream!!

title: tomato pie
directions: Mix biscuit mix and milk; spread in bottom of greased 9-inch pie plate.
Cover tomatoes with boiling water for a few minutes. Peel and slice thinly.
Layer in pie shell.
Top each layer with salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and grated onion.
Continue until pie is level.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese and spread over top of pie.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until nicely browned.
Let set for 10 minutes before slicing.
Add a green salad and you have a great summer lunch or serve as a side dish with hamburgers or steak.

title: endive salad(serves 2)
directions: On individual salad plates, place chopped endive (leave some rounds).
Sprinkle with Bleu cheese and chopped walnuts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce with gelatin and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Cook slightly and add other ingredients.
Add red food coloring, if desired.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch dish or into 4 cup mold.
Chill until set.

title: tacos
directions: Make Beef Filling:
Saute onion and garlic in the 2 tablespoons of oil until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Add tomato, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring frequently, about 10 minutes or until thick and heated thoroughly.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Whirl broccoli in blender until creamy smooth. Mix with cream cheese, horseradish and pimento.

title: winning tea punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine instant tea, water, concentrates and cranberry juice.
Just before serving, add ice.
Makes more than one gallon or 25 (five ounce) servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine Egg Beaters and sweetened condensed milk.
Mix well. Add 3 ounces of Key lime juice a little at a time and blend until filling is smooth and creamy.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve chilled.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams and pour over vegetables in medium saucepan. Add enough water to barely cover; cover and simmer over medium heat until potatoes are tender. Add flour to melted margarine in saucepan; stir until blended, then add half and half. Whisk over heat until smooth and creamy. Add vegetables and clam mixture until heated through. Season with salt, pepper and sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and cream soups together.
Pour over chicken. Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Crush 1 tube Ritz crackers. Mix together.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Wash vegetables and let drain.
Chop all ingredients fine. Cover with a dressing.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat, onion, garlic and pepper with salt and pepper. Stir in raw rice.
Add tomatoes.
Rinse jars with 1 cup water and add.
Put on lid.
Cook slow and stir often for about 1/2 hour until thick and rice is done.

title: oven barbecue brisket
directions: In a small bowl combine the first 8 ingredients and rub on both sides of the beef in a roasting pan.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 10 to 12 hours.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 45 minutes per pound.
Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour to let fat congeal.
When ready to serve, remove beef from pan; remove fat with a slotted spoon.
Reserve meat juices.
Cut beef in thin, even slices across grain and return to pan.

title: cucumber dip(great for gyros)
directions: Combine cheese and milk; beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables or on Gyros.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: bourbon wieners
directions: Cut wieners with bite-size pieces.
Combine the other ingredients.
Pour over wieners and simmer approximately 1 hour. Serve hot.

title: tri-color pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften margarine; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in extracts.
Combine flour and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, beating until thoroughly combined.
Divide batter into thirds.
Add a few drops of red food coloring to 1/3 of the batter, a few drops of green food coloring to the second third, and leave remaining third as is.
Place alternating spoonfuls of batter into well-buttered and floured 12-cup Bundt cake pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Cut through batter with a knife.
Bake 65 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.
Dust top of cake with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Meanwhile, cook bacon in a large skillet.
When crisp, remove and set aside.
Add sausage to skillet and cook until crisp.
Remove and set aside. Add onion, celery and garlic to skillet.
Cook until onion is translucent.
Toss in cooked rice, sausage and bacon.
Mix well and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 5 cups.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Place half of the batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Heat caramels, margarine and milk over low heat, stirring until melted.
Spread on top of baked cake.
Sprinkle chips and nuts over caramel.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake 30 minutes until toothpick comes out batter free.
Cool and ice. Tastes even better the second day!

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Combine ingredients in a large ice cube tray; it will curdle. Allow to freeze.
Beat with mixer and refreeze.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Make a biscuit mixture from any recipe of your choice.
Mix potatoes, onion, corned beef and white sauce; heat.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
The mixture must be hot.
Top with biscuit mixture.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are done per biscuit recipe.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Combine ingredients.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Dough can be refrigerated up to a week.

title: turkey noodle supreme(great leftover recipe)
directions: Cook celery and carrots in a small amount of water until soft. Do not drain.
Add turkey and gravy; cook until heated.
Add about 2 cups water and the uncooked noodles.
Bring to a boil; simmer until noodles are cooked (about 10 to 15 minutes).
You may have to add additional water while noodles are cooking to end up with a stew-like consistency.

title: string bean vegetable casserole
directions: Cook a generous amount of thick bacon until crisp.
Drain, cool and break into pieces.
Save just enough bacon drippings to saute a large batch of chopped onions.
Put all ingredients, except soup, bread crumbs and butter, into a large casserole dish. Mix together with the soup.
Sprinkle the top of the casserole with fresh bread crumbs; dot generously with butter.
Place in a medium oven (about 325°); bake until the casserole starts to bubble and the top is crusty and golden brown.
Serve with a tossed fresh green salad and a dessert for luncheon or for a light supper.

title: hot crab open facers
directions: Stir together crabmeat and mayonnaise; set aside.
Beat together cream cheese, egg yolk, onion, mustard and dash of salt until smooth and creamy.
Spread toasted muffin halves thinly with butter, then with crab mixture.
Top with cream cheese mixture.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and broil 5 to 6 inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes, until top is bubbly and golden.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onions, peppers and garlic. Add and simmer chicken breasts. Add remaining ingredients and simmer. Serve with Fritos or Doritos.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream eggs, oil, shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients. Roll into small balls.
Press down with bottom of glass, dipped in sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° on middle rack for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen cookies.
Works well with 1/2 of recipe.

title: spinach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, mix the thawed spinach (squeeze to remove the extra water), eggs, Italian bread crumbs and Lipton onion soup mix.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Pour olive oil into standard size tin pie pan.
Sprinkle half the Parmesan cheese over the olive oil.
Sprinkle half the Cheddar into the pan. Sprinkle half the Mozzarella cheese into pan.
Place one slice of Swiss cheese in the center.
Spoon spinach mixture over cheese. Place second slice of Swiss cheese in the center over the mixture. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top evenly.
Place on middle rack in preheated oven for 25 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix flour, buttermilk and eggs in a bowl.
Add water a little at a time until mixture is creamy.
Mixture should not be thick. Spray pan with cooking spray (Pam).
When pan is hot (I cook mine on medium-low heat), pour batter into pan with desired size.
Cook on one side until bubbles appear.
Turn over and cook on other side.
This makes about 20 (4-inch) pancakes.
Top with syrup or fruit.

title: mexi-corn bake
directions: In 1-quart ovenware casserole dish, brown onion, pork and beef.
Turn dish, stir and cook for additional 8 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Place in baking dish.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Continue cooking for 15 to 16 minutes or until mixture boils. Stir, then cook for another 10 minutes.
Prepare pastry.
Cover dish with pastry.
Cook 14 to 15 minutes longer.

title: double-quick bean bake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: burritos wrap arounds
directions: Core, rinse, drain and finely shred lettuce.
Cover and chill. When ready to serve, toss lettuce with onion, ham and 1 teaspoon chili powder.
Halve, peel and finely dice avocado.
Stir into dressing along with the remaining 1/4 teaspoon chili powder.

title: black eye pea dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with chips.
It is also great with Chicken, fish, or grilled meat.

title: mixed up salad
directions: Mix marshmallows and sour cream together.
Stir in next six ingredients.
Add enough Cool Whip to make it smooth.

title: lemon fluff dessert
directions: Cut angel food cake into small pieces.
Whip the whipping cream, adding vanilla and sugar as desired.
Fold in condensed milk and lemonade (yellow or pink).

title: sausage meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into small balls.
Bake at 375° on cookie sheet until light brown, about 25 minutes.
Keep fat drained off.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Add ginger ale just before serving.
Cherries may be added, if desired.

title: chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, toss chicken with celery, parsley, salt and pepper to mix well.
Gently fold in whipped cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice and almonds until well combined.
Refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a pan and cook over medium heat until onions and okra are done, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be served over cornbread or rice.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Simmer 20 minutes.
Add 1 (14 1/2 ounce) canned stewed tomatoes and 2/3 cup uncooked pasta.
Simmer 20 minutes more. Serves 4 to 6.
Great with cornbread!

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer.
Keep refrigerated.
Keeps for months in containers.
Makes 2 quarts and one pint.

title: zucchini garden chowder
directions: In soup kettle over medium heat, saute zucchini, onion and parsley in butter until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add bouillon and lemon juice. Mix well and bring to boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes. Add tomatoes, milk and corn. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until corn is tender. Just before serving, stir in cheeses until melted.

title: cherry waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss apples and lemon juice.
Add celery, cherries, cranberries and almonds.
In small bowl, whisk mayo, sour cream, honey and salt until well blended.
Pour over salad and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: blue cheese-bacon potatoes
directions: Cut baked potatoes length-wise.
Scoop out and mash; beat with electric mixer until smooth with all other ingredients.
Fill shells and rebake 15 minutes or until heated throughout.
Top with bacon.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Line an ungreased cookie sheet with roll dough (stretch a little).
Bake at 375° for 11 to 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing and spread over cooled crust. Refrigerate.
Mix together onions, peppers, broccoli and cheese. Spread over top of pizza.
Grate a carrot and sprinkle over top. Press down on pizza with waxed paper.
Cover and refrigerate.
Cut in squares and serve.
Can be made ahead.

title: delicious beef salad
directions: Cut red pepper, carrots and celery in julienne strips.
Place in salad bowl. Add beef and onion. Combine remaining ingredients for dressing. Add to beef mixture.
Marinate for several hours. Serve on lettuce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: monterey spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti. In medium bowl, beat egg and add sour cream, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Drain spaghetti.
Add to egg mixture along with Monterey Jack cheese, spinach and half of onions.
Pour into greased 2-quart dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pound meat between sheets of wax paper with a mallet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and let stand 15 minutes.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in deep frypan.
Add onion and cook over medium heat; stir constantly for about 5 minutes or until softened.
Stir in flour and mustard and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to low, cover pan and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour two 8 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans.
Stir together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in a medium-size bowl; combine flour, baking soda and cinnamon on wax paper.
Stir dry ingredients into liquid just until evenly mixed. Stir in apples and pecans.
Divide between pans.

title: fudge
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar until mixed thoroughly.
Add milk and stir until smooth, then add water and a dash of salt.
Boil until you get firm drops of fudge when dripped into cold water and no discoloration of water, then add 2 tablespoons butter, 1 tablespoon peanut butter and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Stir until partially stiff and then pour into pan.

title: oven potato salad
directions: Mix together all the ingredients, except bacon.
Place in 13 x 10-inch baking dish.
Fry bacon until crisp and then crumble on top of potato mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 8 or more people.

title: pink champagne frozen salad
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar until thoroughly blended.
Fold in Cool Whip (red food coloring may be added, if desired).
Fold in fruits and optional nuts and marshmallows.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: big orange jello
directions: Mix jello according to directions on package for quick set. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: ozark pie
directions: Mix all and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Will rise.
Cool completely; will fall.
Fill dish with softened ice cream (over 1/2 gallon).
Freeze and crush 6 Heath bars.
Sprinkle on ice cream, then freeze.
Serve in servings topped with hot chocolate syrup.

title: pizza popcorn
directions: In saucepan, melt butter with garlic and oregano. Pour over popcorn; mix well and toss with cheese.

title: 4 layer delight dessert
directions: Mix all together and pat down into 9 x 10-inch glass dish. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: sherry gelatine dessert
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
Add boiling water and sugar and stir until gelatine dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into sherbet glasses and chill until firm.
Delicious topped with a dollop of sweetened whipped cream and sprinkled with toasted slivered almonds.

title: deep dish crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 425°. Toss together cheese and flour. Combine milk, eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg. Add crab, cheese mix and spinach to milk mix.
Pour into pie shell. Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake an additional 30 to 35 minutes.

title: multi grains snack bar
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes in lightly sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Optional:
Add chocolate chips, nuts, etc.)

title: bread sticks
directions: Soften margarine then add next 3 ingredients.
Split open hot dog buns and spread butter mixture on buns.
Cut each half in 3 strips.
Bake at 200° over 1 hour.

title: never fail chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil over medium heat. Let cool until right consistency to spread.

title: tuna tater tots
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: finger salad
directions: Spread crescent dough out in sheet pan.
Bake as directed. Allow to cool completely.
Beat together the softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread over crust. Top with chopped veggies and shredded cheese.

title: banana jam
directions: Peel the bananas and thinly slice or mash with a fork. Place the bananas in a heavy saucepan with the lime juice, orange juice, sugar, vanilla bean and salt and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and gently simmer the banana jam until thick, about 30 minutes, stirring often. Stir in the banana liqueur and remove the pan from the heat.

title: yummy afternoon snack
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Melt chocolate.
Pour over dry ingredients; spread over waxed paper.
Let cool; break into small pieces.

title: coconut cream candy
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add milk and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, heating slowly.
Boil 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove and add coconut and vanilla, beating until creamy.
Pour into buttered tins and cool.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in top of double boiler and cook over boiling water until thick.
Cover with lid and cook 15 minutes.
Top with meringue and brown.
This makes 2 pies.

title: mary jezek's bug juice chicken
directions: Cut fryer into serving pieces and place skin side down in ovenproof pan.
Mix soy sauce, lemon juice, onion powder, garlic powder, poultry seasoning and powdered ginger.
Pour over chicken, flip the coated chicken skin side up and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours, basting twice with pan juices.
When chicken is almost done, cook enough egg noodles to serve 4 in boiling water.
Drain noodles; remove chicken to another dish, then dump noodles into oven pan and swoosh them around in soy sauce mixture.
Serve.

title: flank steak a la kenneth
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix together Bristol Cream, water, broth and mushrooms.
Simmer.
Add onions and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add tomato and simmer for another 5 minutes.
Pound steak pieces flat with mallet.
Rub in desired amount of garlic powder, pepper and tomato.
Let sit.
Spray broiling rack with Pam.
Arrange meat on rack and broil until done.
Serve meat on platter.
Pour sauce over steak and enjoy.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream butter, 1 cup of sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture and beat.
Pour half of this mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and line in casserole dish.
Mix cheese, soup, mayonnaise, pepper and bring to a boil.
Pour over broccoli and sprinkle crushed cracker crumbs over top or use canned onion rings in place of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Layer the bottom of your casserole dish with chips.
After boiling chicken, cut it up and put it over the chips.
In a separate bowl, combine 2 cans of soup and sour cream.
Pour sour cream and soup over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, cover with cheese and melt.

title: pumpkin ricotta cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor or mix well in a large bowl.
Pour batter into a 10-inch spring-form pan (you may want to spray the pan lightly with cooking spray, but you don't have to).
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool on a rack and then chill for 3 hours.
Serve cold.

title: yellow jello cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed; divide equally into 3 (8-inch) round layer cake pans and bake as directed.
(Cakes may take less time than indicated when divided 3 ways.)
Set aside 2 layers.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water (cool).
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add slowly with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch pans that have been well-greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef.
Add salt and pepper and drain grease.
Add taco mix (do not add water).
Add tomatoes and Mexican tomatoes, cutting into small pieces.
Add tomato soup.
Add kidney beans and corn.
Mix and bring to a boil.

title: chocolate crunch cake
directions: Mix favorite chocolate cake and put batter in round cake pans. Top with following before baking:
graham cracker crumbs, melted oleo, chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake cake as usual.
May serve frosted or frost with whipped cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine and beat together first 5 ingredients; add dry ingredients, nuts and raisins. Mix thoroughly. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Sift together sugar and cocoa.
Put in microwave-safe container.
Put margarine and evaporated milk on top.
Do not stir.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and mix well.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Put into buttered 8 x 8-inch dish and refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: caramel sauce dip for fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir over medium heat until mixture boils.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes, stirring often.
Makes about 1 pint. Excellent with apple or banana slices.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown steak in bite size pieces.
Add other ingredients. Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake until golden brown, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: walnut sherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed, then beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour half of the batter into well-greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with half of topping.
Spread the other half of batter.
Sprinkle and cover with other half of topping.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: almond cream
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Heat 1 1/2 cups water, the milk and the sugar to boiling.
Add the dissolved gelatin and the almond extract.
Mix well.
Pour the mixture into an 8-inch square pan.
Freeze or refrigerate until the mixture is firm.
Cut the mixture into cubes.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in frozen block of strawberries until separated.
Mix with beater for 1 minute. Pour in mold.
Make Dream Whip according to directions on box.
Use 1 (3-ounce) package Jell-O.
Dissolve Jell-O in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup ice cubes and stir until slightly thickened. Take out any unmelted ice cubes.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour over Jell-O in mold.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients but nuts.
Make into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add remaining butter or margarine, broccoli, Cheez Whiz, soup and rice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and for 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Lightly grease an 8-inch pan; set aside.
Put sugar and cocoa in another microwave or glass dish; mix well.
Add milk and oleo to this; do not stir.
Heat, uncovered, in microwave oven for 2 minutes on High.
After cooking, stir just enough to combine ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir until well blended.
Pour into reserved pan; refrigerate for 1 hour before cutting.

title: crab stuffed morel mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine stuffing mixture in a bowl large enough to enable thorough mixing.
Carefully slice each morel lengthwise along one side only (do not cut through both sides).
If using cap-type mushrooms as a substitute, remove the stems and fill each cap, bottom side up, with the mixture..

title: marinated green beans and onion salad
directions: Mix well. Cover and chill for several hours.

title: sunday roast
directions: Brown roast that has been floured, salted, peppered and garlicked.
Put roast in baking pan with water to the top of roast. Cook at 300° to 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes and onions.
Squirt ketchup on top.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.
This will make your tongue slap your brains out.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes 1 1/2 hours in a 425° oven.
Slice in half and then in quarters; remove most of the pulp, but leave some in.
Put skins in deep fryer until crisp.
Remove.
Brush inside with butter.
Put cheese and bacon bits in skins.
Place in oven long enough for cheese to melt.
Serve with sour cream.

title: peanut butter cream cheese dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Mix in peanut butter.
Stir in the Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate for at least two hours.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover the bottom of a greased jelly roll pan, 17 x 11-inches, with the rolls, pressing together.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing; spread over rolls.
Sprinkle vegetables over top of cream cheese, then sprinkle cheese on top.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours or overnight. Cut into small square bars.

title: dill dip in round bread
directions: Combine yogurt and cottage cheese in blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in seasonings and refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Hollow out the center of one loaf (about the size of a 2 cup measure) and use it as your serving container.
Cut the removed section of bread and the second loaf into cubes to use as dippers.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan.
Combine milk, flour and sugar. Mix well and add to melted margarine.
Add peaches.
Do not stir. Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Excellent when served while warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: orange sauce
directions: Mix well and pour over baked cake as soon as cake has been removed from oven.
Let cake and sauce stand overnight before serving.

title: good squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick oleo and 1 egg. Press in bottom of pan that has been sprayed with Pam or equivalent.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and 1 box confectioners sugar. Bake at 325° to 350° until done, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: onion wine soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onions and mix well.
Add beef broth, celery leaves and potato.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Puree mixture in a blender.
Return to saucepan.
Blend in wine, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in cream, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bruchetta
directions: Mix chopped tomatoes, chopped olives, garlic, salt and pepper and mix in olive oil. (Hint: The greener the olive oil, the better the quality.) Cut bread into slices and lay slices on baking sheet. Spread butter on slices. Spoon on tomato olive mixture on top of slices. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Place in oven at low temperature to warm. Serve warm.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour until thick.
Pour into 2 baked
pie shells.	Slice bananas over pineapple.
Sprinkle with cherries, coconut and nuts.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: melted moments
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cornstarch.
Blend in butter until well blended.
Shape into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°.
Very gently while cookies are hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook meat, drain and add pizza sauce and tomato sauce for later use.
Combine cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with a layer of noodles then layer the cheese then a layer of meat.
Add another layer of noodles, then cheese and meat.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until noodles seem tender when tested with a fork.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes in approximately 3/4-inch slices orange juice, grated orange rind, sugar and corn starch, mixed with a bit of cold water, in small pan and bring to a boil, stirring to prevent sticking.
Pour this mixture over the sweet potatoes, dot with slices of butter or margarine and cover with thin orange slices.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon, do not use beater. Batter will be stiff.
Spread into floured, greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or frost with icing.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil and stir in the peanut butter. Remove from heat and stir in the Rice Krispies.
Pack down in greased cake pan.
Melt the chocolate and butterscotch bits over hot water.
Spread over Karo syrup mixture.
Cut when cool.

title: pat's potatoes
directions: Note:
Use O'Brien potatoes with onions and peppers.

title: simply cheesecake
directions: Prepare spring-form pan with margarine and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: popovers
directions: Sift flour and salt together; set aside.
In a small bowl whisk together eggs and milk.
Add milk mixture to flour while stirring.
Stir until smooth.

title: honey ginger carrots
directions: Heat carrots and water to boiling in a 12-inch skillet; reduce heat and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Drain and remove carrots.
Stir in butter, honey, lemon juice, ginger and salt; heat until bubbly.
Add carrots and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally until carrots are glazed, about 5 minutes.

title: easy rocky road fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine the chocolate chips, milk and butter. Cook and stir over medium heat until chips are melted and the mixture is smooth.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in peanuts and marshmallows.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yield: about 3 1/4 pounds.

title: kidney bean and corn chowder
directions: About 30 minutes before serving:
In a 5-quart saucepan, over medium heat in hot oil, cook onion and garlic for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini or summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in squash mix.
Combine stuffing and oleo.
Spread half in pan, then spoon all vegetable mixture over this.
Put remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top (enough to cover top of casserole).
Place a few pats of butter over crackers. Bake 20 minutes or until crackers are golden brown.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: ham and egg casserole
directions: In a double boiler, melt the butter or margarine.
Add the flour and the seasoning and blend.
Add the milk and the minced onion and green pepper. These will cook as the sauce does.
Add the mushrooms and the dry mustard.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine mixture, then refrigerate 5 minutes.
Roll out.
Makes 2 double 9-inch crusts.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Cook butter and sugar together until smooth and well blended. Cool until lukewarm.
Add egg (unbeaten); beat well.
Add flour sifted with baking powder.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.
Cut into squares; cool before removing from pan. Yields 24.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil. Add meats and generously salt and pepper. Add parsley (crush in your hand before adding) and grated cheese. Cook thoroughly; meat should taste very heavily seasoned. Add tomato paste and stir well. Add tomato sauce and 1 large can of water. Simmer with pot lid cracked open a little for approximately 3 hours, stirring frequently.

title: fancy chicken
directions: Put rice in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix pineapple in cream of mushroom soup and orange juice.
Put chicken on top.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: shrimp in angel hair pasta
directions: Melt margarine in a 2 quart saucepan; saute onion and celery until clear.
Add flour and blend to make a smooth paste.
Add half and half slowly stirring constantly.
Add seasoning and chicken broth and cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add shrimp. Return to heat and cook until heated thoroughly.
Serve a generous amount over pasta and garnish lightly with green onions and parsley.

title: meat and bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix with other ingredients. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the butter, shortening, confectioners sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour and salt. Divide dough in half; blend food coloring into one half.

title: quick muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix just until blended; batter should be lumpy.
Spoon into 6 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until muffins are lightly browned.

title: hawaiian supreme cake
directions: Sift cake and pudding mix together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add oil, then 7-Up.
Mix all together and pour into 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with 1 tablespoon milk.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Serve cold over crackers.

title: caramel banana pudding
directions: Caramelize the sweetened condensed milk by preferred method. In a large mixer bowl, combine caramelized milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of the wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding.
Cover and chill.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage; cook and drain.
Line bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan with crescent rolls firmly pressing perforations to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and pepper; pour over.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Serve immediately.
This can be assembled the night before in casserole dish.
Refrigerate.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place hash browns in casserole dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over hash browns.
Bake in
a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Crush the Ritz crackers.
Mix with melted margarine.
Place on top of casserole and bake 10 more minutes.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl; blend at low speed.
Beat at medium speed 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until top springs.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing.

title: zucchini meat loaf
directions: Combine
all
ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Put into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, or I use 2 quart casserole dish. Bake at 350°
for 1 1/4 hours.
You may garnish with zucchini slices sprinkled
with
paprika
last
minutes of baking. Makes
a pretty
dish.
Makes
delicious
sandwiches, if left over.
Very moist and tasty.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
I freeze zucchini to make
this
year
round.
I
shred
or
grate raw zucchini and drain well and package 2 cups per package.

title: greek egg lemon soup
directions: In a saucepan, heat soup and water to boiling.
Turn down low. In a small bowl, beat eggs and lemon juice together.
Pour a little of hot soup into egg mixture, while stirring all the while. Gradually, add egg mixture into the hot soup very slowly, constantly stirring.
(Egg may curdle if too fast.)
Serve at once.
Makes 3 cups of soup.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Add 1 1/3 cups of coconut after beating.
Bake in a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Place on a serving tray.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Put chicken in cake pan and salt and pepper it.
Mix soups and sour cream together and put them on top of the chicken.
Then spread mushrooms on top of the soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cover with foil.

title: real good french fries
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch strips. Rinse in cold water and dry thoroughly before cooking (drying them well is the key to a crispy French fry). In a deep fryer or flat-bottomed wok, fry until halfway done and remove before potatoes start turning yellow. Let them drain. (Fries can be frozen at this point for future use.) When almost ready to serve, finish frying until golden brown and let drain again before adding salt to taste. Serves 4 to 6 (or use 2 to 3 servings and freeze remainder for future use).

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Heat corn syrup with sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add peanut butter and butterscotch candy.
After the candy has melted, add the Special K cereal. Pour in an oblong pan.
Spread candy coating on top.
Cut into squares and store in airtight container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and chicken.
Debone chicken and mix all ingredients together.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.
Then sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: south of the border pie
directions: Saute bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Crumble; set aside.
Mix ground beef lightly with onion and brown.
Add crumbled bacon, tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Prepare corn muffin mix, following label directions for muffins.
Spread 1/2 batter evenly over bottom of greased shallow 6-cup baking dish.
Spoon hot meat mixture over.
Drop remaining batter by tablespoon on top.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 35 minutes or until top is puffed and golden brown.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pesto sauce
directions: In the mixing bowl of a food processor or blender, put the garlic, salt, basil, pinenuts and olive oil and process until smooth, scraping down sides one or two times.
Add the cheeses and butter and process very briefly, just to incorporate the cheeses and butter.
Add 2 tablespoons of the boiling water in which the pasta was cooked.
If sauce is still too thick, add a little more water.
Process for 1 or 2 seconds.
The sauce is now ready for the cooked pasta.

When draining the pasta, just before mixing with the pesto sauce, allow the pasta to be moist with water, don't shake out the colander to rid the pasta of all the liquid. Put pesto first in a warm pasta bowl; add the pasta and toss well to coat the strands.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve with garlic bread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; bring to boil.
Take off heat and mix in peanut butter.
Pour over and mix.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: apple dessert pizza
directions: Cut a 15 in. circle of heavy foil, or use a pizza pan.
Make pastry for 2 crust pie.
Roll out on foil to fit circle; crimp edges as for pie.
Overlap apple slices on top of pastry, covering completely.
Combine 1/2 c. sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg and sprinkle over apples.
Combine flour, 1/2 c. sugar and margarine till crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 450° for 20-25 minutes until crust is brown and apples tender.
Top with ice cream if desired.

title: overnight salad
directions: Wash lettuce and cauliflower; dry well.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Break cauliflower into small pieces.
Place on top of lettuce.
Slice onion and separate into rings; layer on top of cauliflower.

Ring pepper and layer on top of onion. Sprinkle on bacon and shredded cheese, then sprinkle on sugar. Use enough mayonnaise to completely cover the top of the salad. Cover bowl and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Just before serving, stir and mix well.

title: chocolate strawberry pie
directions: Beat dry pudding and pie filling with yogurt and skim milk with a wire whisk or spoon until thickened.
Fold in whipped topping and crushed cookies.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Freeze at least 4 hours.
Remove from freezer about 10 minutes before serving.
Top with fresh strawberries and chocolate curls, as garnish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 13 x 9 pan with cooking spray. Mix the squash, Bisquick, grated Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley, vegetable oil and eggs together and spread in the pan. Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together until blended.
Mix the pecans, cinnamon and sugar.
Spread half of batter in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 sugar mixture, then remaining batter and rest of sugar mixture.
Swirl through with knife like marble cake.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes. Freezes well.

title: christmas chip 'n cherry cake
directions: Beat eggs; stir in sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine with chocolate pieces, nuts, dates and cherries.
Fold in egg-sugar mixture.
Turn into greased and waxed paper-lined large loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Place pan of water on bottom oven rack while baking cake.
Bake cake on top rack at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in Crisco; put water and egg in a cup.
Mix together thoroughly.
Add to flour mixture.
Add vinegar.
Mix well.
Roll out to fit pie pans.
Makes 5 to 6 pie crusts.
Freeze dough that is not used.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli in small pieces (frozen broccoli can be used). Add broccoli to chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Chop onion and celery fine and saute in 1/4 cup butter until soft.
Add to broth.
Add 2 cups milk and bring to simmer. Do not boil.
Thicken with flour and water.

title: stove top cobbler
directions: Bring to
a boil and add salt.
Make regular pie dough, roll out, cut in small pieces and drop in hot berries.
DO NOT stir. If
juice
is
not
thick
enough, stir in 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Cook on low heat just until dough is done.

title: baled hay
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; let stand in salt water overnight.
In morning, drain well.
Bring remaining ingredients (syrup) to boil; drop in vegetables.
Simmer 15 minutes, then can.

title: french creme mint brownies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Blend eggs, chocolate syrup, flour and baking powder.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until crust turns loose from sides of pan.

title: sparkling party punch
directions: Jello color determines color of the punch.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water, lemon juice and extract.
Using a funnel, pour these ingredients into a gallon container.
Add the pineapple juice and shake to mix.
Slowly add the ginger ale, leaving some room to expand.
All the ginger ale will not fit, but save and add to your punch bowl later.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Dissolve soda with milk.	Add
flour
(reserve 1 cup flour), spices and milk (plus milk	or
brandy)
alternately.
Dredge
fruit with reserved flour.
Add fruit and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 300°.

title: taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Stir in taco mix (dry), tomato sauce, corn and 1 cup cheese.
Crush tortilla chips over top.
Spread evenly.
Top with saved cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with Ranch dressing on top if wanted.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Good and moist!

title: ice cream brownie pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts.
Beat for 5 minutes. Stir in nuts, then pour batter into a buttered 8-inch pie tin. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Slice and serve with a big scoop of ice cream.

title: mrs. filbert's lemon coffeecake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Add Mrs. Filbert's, buttermilk and lemon rind.
Beat until smooth. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold in.
Turn into a 10-inch greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes until a cake tester inserted in cake comes out clean. Cool on rack 15 minutes and remove from pan.
In a small bowl, combine confectioners sugar and lemon juice. Stir until smooth.
When cake is completely cool, drizzle with lemon glaze and garnish as desired.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in heavy pot.
Saute onions, pepper and celery until onions are clear.
Add 1/8 cup water and simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Add crawfish and other seasonings to blend.
Serve over hot steamed rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: split pea soup
directions: Bring water, split green peas, baby lima beans, barley, onion, bay leaves, celery seed, carrots, celery and beef stew seasoning mix to a boil in a large stockpot; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, paprika, parsley flakes, basil and pepper; stir and continue cooking an additional hour.

title: melt in mouth pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar.
Mix well, beating in eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring last.
Bake in greased and floured tube, Bundt or loaf pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: grandma's best yet dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk; let cool. Mix 1 egg, sugar, oil and salt. Put yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/3 cup lukewarm water into a bowl and allow to activate. Blend milk, egg mixture and yeast mixture with 4 cups of flour. Knead well. Let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour). Make rolls. Let rise again. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter dip
directions: Mix together and microwave on HIGH for 30 seconds or until warm. Stir well and use as a dip for fresh fruit such as apples, pears and bananas. Very easy for kids and good for them!

title: mexican fruit salad
directions: Stir fruit together in a bowl.
Prepare dressing by mxing together oil, red wine vinegar, sugar, salt and chili powder; mix well.
Pour dressing over the fruit and toss well.
Chill until serving time.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Parmesan cheese with garlic salt.
Add pimento, bell pepper and pecans.
Roll in paprika, chili powder or parsley flakes.

title: chunky fruit salad
directions: Mix Tang and pudding together in large mixing bowl.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice, and measure to make 1 cup.
If pineapple did not have enough juice, finish with juice from drained mandarin oranges.
Add juice to pudding and Tang mixture.
Beat with rotary beater until it thickens (about a minute or 2).
Add drained pineapple and oranges.
Cut bananas into 1-inch chunks and add to other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: baked corn
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
(Do not drain corn.)
Place mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole and bake for 1 hour or until completely set.

title: bow ties
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and Crisco.
Mix like you would for a pie crust.
Beat the egg, vanilla and milk together. Make a well with the flour.
Put the eggs, vanilla and milk; mix well.
Roll out the dough a little at a time and cut in strips. Make a slit in the middle and pull through like a bow tie.
Deep fry in oil and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening, sugar and eggs. Sift together and add 2 cups flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1 teaspoon salt and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.

title: beef and noodles in sour cream
directions: Cook onions in oil until tender.
Add meat and brown.
Add noodles and other ingredients except sour cream.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer over low heat 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in sour cream just before serving and heat but do not boil.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and egg.
Peel and slice peaches.
Place peaches in unbaked pie crust.
Spread prepared icing over peaches.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: microwave pork vegetable roast
directions: Place roast in 4-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with garlic, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, on cook level 3 or on Defrost level or Low cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until thoroughly cooked.
Temperature of 170° should be reached. Turn roast over halfway through cooking time.
This recipe is for a 650 watt microwave.
Level 3 is 195 watts, with pork because it is thoroughly cooked.

title: chili macaroni
directions: In large skillet, brown beef, onion and pepper in small amount of oil; drain.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes, water, chili powder, salt and macaroni.
Cover; simmer gently for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Just before serving, top with cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy.
Flour with love and kindly service.
Fold in 4 cups prayer and faith. After pouring all this into daily life, bake well with the heart of human kindness.
Serve with a smile, anytime and it will satisfy the hunger of starved souls.
Acknowledge Him always in all things.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix corn flakes and half of the melted margarine.
Set aside. Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle corn flake mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: monkey bread
directions: Use tube or Bundt pan.
Grease pan.
Cover bottom of pan with nuts.
Cut half of the biscuits in quarters.
Combine sugar and cinnamon, roll biscuits in mixture and place on nuts.
Add another layer of pecans and the remaining biscuits (prepared).
Melt brown sugar and butter in saucepan.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Break bread to eat.
Do not cut it.

title: crabmeat ring appetizer
directions: Heat mushroom soup, crabmeat and celery.
Add dissolved gelatin/water mixture and heat!
Add everything else.
Pour into well oiled mold (Pam okay).
Chill; best if made the day ahead. Unmold on lettuce bed or surround with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: fiddlehead soup
directions: Bring large pot of salted water to boil.
Add fiddleheads, return to boil and cook until almost tender and pale green, 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Coarsely chop and set aside.
Melt butter over medium heat.
Add onions and cook 5 minutes.
Add fiddleheads and chicken stock.
Bring to gentle boil.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add milk and reduce heat to simmer.
Do not boil at this point.
Stir in remaining and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Mix together all liquid ingredients.
Mix both liquid and dry ingredients.
Pour mixture into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together for liquid.

title: old fashioned pot pie
directions: Prepare crust according to package directions (for a double crusted pie) using a 9 inch pie pan.

In a 2 quart pot, melt butter and saute 1/2 cup onion and 1/2 cup mushroom until soft. Add mixture of drained vegetables, mushroom soup, sour cream, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1/2 teaspoon sage and cooked turkey.
Mix well and place filling into bottom of pie shell.
Follow package directions for topping pie with second piece of pastry.
Bake for 35 - 45 minutes until golden brown.
It may be necessary to cover loosely with foil for a portion of cooking time so crust doesn't burn.

title: squash rolls
directions: Cook squash whole in a little water; drain and mash.
Add sugar, salt, beaten eggs and cracker crumbs.

title: baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 3-quart oblong baking dish.
In a medium bowl or in the jar, stir together the sauce and herb seasoning.
Remove 2 cups and set aside.
Stir remaining mixture into pasta.
Place half of the pasta mixture in baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup of the Mozzarella cheese on top.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add pecans and stir until all are coated.
Put on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 275° for 25 to 30 minutes.
If some of mixture is not used, add more pecans to it and coat them.
Place about 2-inches apart on pan.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Cream the cream cheese until fluffy with liquid and mayonnaise.
Add nuts and olives.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour for flavors to meld.
Use as sandwich filling or topping for snack crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender.
Pour off water.
Put onion in oleo to saute; don't brown.
Save enough oleo to grease casserole.
Mix squash, onion and eggs with sugar and 1/2 of crackers.
Put in casserole.
Cover top with rest of crackers.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 30 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: In a large skillet, brown the chicken wings in the hot butter. Cover and cook until tender.
In a saucepan, gently boil together the orange juice, 1 tablespoon honey, soy sauce and garlic until thickened, about 15 minutes.
Stir in the remaining honey.
Remove garlic and pour mixture over the wings.
Turn them over low heat until they are glazed.

title: no cook pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and cream cheese in large mixing bowl. Mix 1/2 of this mixture with pie filling in another bowl.
Pour in crusts.
Pour remaining Cool Whip mixture on top.
Refrigerate.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix soup, mushrooms, pimentos, mayonnaise and seasonings. Layer alternately with hard-boiled eggs, bacon (or sausage) in a 3-quart casserole.
End with sauce on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serve with fried apples and hot biscuits.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls (about 2 measuring tablespoons) of dough 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies (they will be light and moist; do not overcook), 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool on baking sheet for 2 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: beef-n-chicken casserole
directions: Layer dried beef, chicken breasts and bacon.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and drain grease.
Mix sour cream and cream of mushroom soup.
Spread on top of casserole. Return to oven and bake an additional 45 minutes.

title: almond chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice for sauce.
Combine pineapple with chicken, celery, green pepper and almonds in 2-quart casserole.
Combine reserved pineapple juice with enough chicken bouillon to measure 2 cups.
Add sherry, soy sauce, cornstarch, ginger and garlic powder.
Stir well to dissolve cornstarch; pour over chicken mixture and mix well.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until sauce has thickened, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato wedges and sprinkle with green onion.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until heated through.
Serve over rice, if desired. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sandi groberg's chocolate torte
directions: Melt in microwave or double boiler and stir until smooth.
Pour into prepared torte shells.
Refrigerate.

title: beet mold
directions: Drain beets, reserving beets.
Mix juice with 7-Up to produce 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Bring vinegar, liquid, Jell-O, salt and sugar to a near boil.
When cool, add horseradish and beets.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan or approximate size pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: azteca casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; add onions and green pepper.
Cook until onion is clear.
Add corn, barbecue sauce and chili powder; mix well and heat through.
Place 1 cup corn chips in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with 1/2 of meat mixture, then 2/3 cup Cheez Whiz.
Repeat chips and meat and top with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 375°
for 25 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins in sugar water (about 2 cups of water) until raisins swell up and get soft, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed.
Bake pie shell and let cool.
After shell and raisins are cool, mix raisins and vanilla pudding together.
Pour in pie shell.
Can top with meringue.
