title: scallop potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens.
Add potatoes; let boil, stirring constantly.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
If desired, add parsley flakes and onion flakes.
Crumble 1 slice of cheese and sprinkle on top.

title: green beans
directions: Cut and string about a quart of green beans in 1-inch pieces. Wash 4 times and put into iron pot.
Cut slice of bacon into 1/2-inch pieces.
Put into pot and add water until you can see it. Add salt and cook until tender.
When tender, remove lid and cook out excess water.
Cook on medium while you work around the house.

title: date pudding
directions: Combine brown sugar and water; cook to form a thin syrup. Boil 3 to 5 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice and cook carrots in salted boiling water for 10 minutes. Drain and add butter.
Stir until melted, then stir in cheese and onion.
Place in buttered casserole dish. Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Mix soups, sour cream and hamburger.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with cheese. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Cover with tomato soup, cream of mushroom soup and Lipton onion soup mix, mixed together.
Add approximately 1 can of water. Simmer in skillet for 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: pennsylvania dutch corn bread
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Add corn meal and mix well.
Blend eggs, milk and shortening together until smooth. Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni-cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; salt and drain.
Stir egg in glass; salt and pepper.
Stir.
Add milk; stir.
Layer in round Pyrex dish the macaroni and cheese; pour half of milk mixture over.
Layer macaroni and cheese; pour remaining milk mixture over.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on top.
Bake, covered, in 450° oven for 40 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in layers in a large bowl as listed.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour over top of layers and let stand overnight.

title: egg flower soup
directions: Dissolve the cornstarch in 1/3 cup of the cold broth.
Bring the rest of broth to a boil, then add cornstarch mixture, stirring.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat and add sugar, salt, sherry and soy sauce.
Pour in the beaten eggs in a slow stream. Stir slowly and they will separate into shreds.
Add green onions.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Add sugar slowly to margarine in a large bowl, beating well (300 times). Beat in one egg until smooth.
Add other egg and beat well (300 times), add half the flour mixture, half the milk and the vanilla. Mix 50 times.
Add rest of the flour mixture and milk.
Mix until smooth (200 times).
Fill a greased, floured baking pan or 2 layer pans no more than half full.
Bake at 375° (moderate oven) 25 to 35 minutes, until cake springs back when lightly touched near center.

title: coconut chew-chews (cookies)
directions: Beat together 1/2 cup brown sugar, shortening, egg yolk and vanilla.
Stir in flour sifted with salt and baking powder.
Pat firmly over bottom of a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, salt, sugar, eggs, margarine, and vanilla thoroughly.
Pour into buttered baking dish.

title: mushroom dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sour cream.
Gradually add sour cream to the consistency you want your dip, thinner for chips or thicker for crackers.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except tortillas and cheeses. Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and grease.
Layer bottom with tortillas.
Put layer of mixed ingredients with 1/2 of cheeses, then another layer of meat mixture with rest of cheese on top. Bake until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: stir-crazy chocolate cake
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients in a square, nonstick cake pan.
Stir well.
Pour the water, vinegar and vanilla directly into the pan.
Stir with a spoon in a circular motion until all the ingredients are well blended.
Level with spoon, bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Exchange:
1 bread.
Yields 12 servings.

title: salad de mexico
directions: Saut the ground meat and taco mix. Cool and add the onion, chopped pepper, Italian dressing and pinto beans. Marinate overnight. Next day, add the remaining ingredients before serving. Toss together.

title: crispy chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line large shallow baking pan with aluminum foil.
Cut wings at each point.
Discard tips.
Melt Crisco in lined pan.
Combine flour, onion salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Add chicken pieces, few at a time, shake well. Place pieces in pan.
Bake 25 minutes, turn and bake 20 - 25 minutes. Drain on paper towel.
Serve with barbecue sauce.

title: yummy crunchies(dieter's sin)
directions: Melt butter and add sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Cook for 3 minutes exactly.
Pour over layer of crackers in large shallow baking dish or pan (greased).
Bake for 15 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Remove and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Wait 5 minutes and then spread evenly over top.
Cool and break into pieces or cut into bars.

title: hobo stew
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onions. After beef is browned, add ketchup and mustard. Stir in brown sugar and simmer. Serve warm over toasted bread.

title: pioneer fruit cobbler(pioneer no-fat bisquick)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8 x 8-inch pan with vegetable oil (Pam or other).
Spread pie filling in pan.
Combine Bisquick mix, sugar and milk.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of fruit.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown.
I added a dollop of Promise no-fat margarine to top of each spoonful.

title: honey and spice chicken
directions: Brush chicken with butter; place skin side down in shallow baking dish.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Combine 57 Sauce and honey.
Turn chicken skin side up; brush with half of honey mixture.
Bake chicken for 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Brush again with honey mixture.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: vegetable chicken soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil. Saute chicken until slightly brown. Remove chicken to a bowl. Add onions, garlic and carrots to the pan, stirring until onions begin to soften. Return chicken to pan along with cauliflower, tomatoes and broth. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes. Stir in spinach, chili sauce or hot sauce and simmer an additional 5 minutes.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add brown sugar, salt and fat.
Let cool, then add yeast.
Add white flour and wheat flour.
Stir and then knead the last of the flour into the dough.
Put into a greased or oiled pan or crockery (turn over to oil the top of the dough).
Cover with Saran Wrap or damp cloth.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rise again.
Shape into 2 large loaves or 4 small loaves.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Stir over low heat until thick.
Flavor with nutmeg or lemon and pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg white (1), add one tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon lemon extract and fold in.
Pour mixture over pie and brown.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Select a large, nonstick skillet with a tight fitting lid. Remove all skin and visible fat from chicken.
Combine flour and spices in plastic bag or bowl.
Shake or roll chicken in seasoned flour.
Coat all chicken before heating oil, then heat oil in skillet and add chicken.
Brown over medium heat about 10 to 12 minutes per side until golden brown on all sides.
Add 1/2 cup water to chicken.
Cover tightly.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Remove cover.
Turn up heat and cook off remaining liquid.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil.
Add water, tomato sauce and thinly sliced onions.
Cover.
Cook slowly over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover.
Continue cooking about 1 hour or until tender.

title: sensation hot crab meat dip
directions: 1. Mix all ingredients together.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Miracle Whip together.
Mix well. Add enough Miracle Whip to moisten.

title: ruth dodge-ducharme's breakfast pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Have ready a 10-inch pie plate.
Crumble sausage into a large skillet.
Cook over medium heat 5 to 7 minutes, breaking up clumps, until cooked through and lightly browned.
Remove from skillet with a slotted spoon, pressing out excess fat.
Spoon into pie plate.

title: pork cantonese casserole
directions: Layer the pork strips in a greased 6 1/2 x 10 x 2-inch casserole.
Next, layer the celery, onion and top with the green pepper rings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, orange and sugar.
Add celery, marshmallows, pecans and apple.
Mix raspberry jello with hot water and mix with cranberry mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: indian fried bread
directions: Mix together to make a stiff dough.
Make a ball about 3 inches in diameter and pull the ball into a 6-inch circle with the fingers.
Do not use a rolling pin.
Slash one side from the center out with a sharp knife in the bread in five places.
Heat 2 inches of cooking oil in a skillet and, when hot, drop in the bread.
Brown on each side and drain.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sour milk; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; beat well. Stir in zucchini.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle on top 1 cup miniature chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken creole
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter until onion is tender but not browned.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes, bay leaf, sugar, seasoned salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce; bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add chicken and heat.
Blend cornstarch and water; stir in.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add parsley and serve.
Good with hot, cooked brown or white rice, a green salad and French bread and yum-yum.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients together and form into a loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: speedie roll dough
directions: Combine water, sugar & yeast, stir until dissolved. Add salt & 2 cups flour; beat for 2 minutes with beater. Add eggs & shortening & beat for 1 minute. Work in remaining flour.
Let rise.
This dough is excellent for cinnamon rolls or sweet rolls. Bake as for rolls, or cinnamon rolls, etc.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate in butter.
Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Beat well.
Put in an unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, toss the hot spaghetti with the olive oil.
In a small bowl, combine the eggs and the 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Stir into the spaghetti.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and onion together.
Spread mixture on a slice of ham.
Then roll ham up and slice, arrange on tray, insert toothpick into each pinwheel and serve.

title: saucy cranberry chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with 1 tablespoon flavor enhancer.
In a pie plate, mix together flour, cornmeal, salt, pepper and paprika. Coat chicken.

title: coconut or chocolate
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thickens and pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla for meringue and bake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Skin and defat chicken.
Cut into small pieces about one inch long. Cut carrots in long pieces; cut celery diagonally.
Dice onions and peppers.
Mix with mayonnaise, 2 cups of broth and mushroom soup.
Cook rice with the other 2 cups of chicken broth.

title: hot cheese cookies
directions: Mix ingredients by hand or mixer.
Dough will be stiff.
Roll into 4 thin rounds in wax paper. Chill or freeze.

title: rice krispie-peanut butter candy
directions: Mix the sugar and syrup together in 3-quart pan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until it comes to a boil, then let cook 1 minute without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Mix in peanut butter. Pour into a large pot in which Rice Krispies have already been put.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
When finished, lift each piece of candy so it doesn't stick to paper.
Let cool, then put in airtight container with waxed paper between layers.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put 2/3 of batter in cookie sheet.
Top with 2 large cans cherry (or your favorite) pie filling.
Put the remaining batter in spots on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Sift confectioners sugar into a large mixing bowl.
Measure remaining ingredients into the same bowl. Blend on medium speed until all ingredients have been thoroughly mixed together. Scrape sides of bowl when necessary. Blend an additional minute.

title: rye boat
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with rye bread.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook sausage and add other ingredients.
Serve warm with nacho chips.

title: dietetic smackaroons
directions: Beat egg whites with baking powder until stiff, but not dry. Blend in flour, artificial sweetener, almond extract, cereal and coconut.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: potato-sausage-apple skillet(serves 4)
directions: In large skillet or frypan heat oil.
Brown sausage lightly. Remove and reserve.
Add onion, potatoes and caraway seed, tossing lightly to coat with oil.
Cover.
Cook on medium heat 10 minutes. Uncover.
Stir through.
Recover and cook 10 minutes more. Uncover.
Add apple slices, parsley, chives, salt, pepper and reserved sausage.

title: million dollar dessert
directions: Make crust of flour, oleo, brown sugar and chopped pecans. Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: country green beans
directions: Drain liquid from beans, measuring 1 1/3 cups liquid and save. Saute onion in butter in medium sized frying pan, just until soft. Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in measured liquid from beans and evaporated milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce thickens and boil one minute.
Stir in green beans, heating slowly, stirring often, about ten minutes or until bubbly hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except poppy seed, with mixer until smooth.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour into Bundt pan, which has been greased and sprinkled with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together.
Add cracker crumbs and sugar.
Smooth in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator.
Melt 12 ounces chocolate chips and pour over mixture.
Put in refrigerator exactly 30 minutes.
Cut in small pieces and refrigerate.
Freezes well.

title: sugar-free lemon cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese. Bring water to a boil and add to gelatin. Stir until thoroughly dissolved. Add milk to pudding mix and blend. Add gelatin and cream cheese to pudding mix and beat with mixer until well blended. Pour into baked pie crusts and chill until firm.

title: meat loaf no. 1
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding 1/2 can of the mushroom soup. Mix thoroughly.
Shape into loaf.
Place in aluminum loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until brown as you like. Blend remaining mushroom soup with 3 tablespoons drippings and 1/4 cup of water.
Stir.
Serve this sauce as hot gravy on meat loaf slices.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place pork chops in casserole dish.
Slice potatoes in thin slices.
Place in a layer on pork chops. Sprinkle diced onion on potatoes.
Take drippings and make flour gravy.
Pour over pork chops and potatoes.
Bake for 40 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: dirty rice
directions: Fry sausage, onion, and pepper in a large skillet. Do not drain, unless there is a lot of grease. Add rice, tabasco sauce, salt and pepper. Serve with corn bread and red beans.

title: breakfast french puffs
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Use well-greased cupcake liners; fill 1/2 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt oleo; stir cinnamon and sugar together in a bowl.
Dip puffs into oleo and then in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Freezes well.
Makes about 30 puffs.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Crumble bread in milk; add salt and pepper to ground beef. Form into medium balls.
Place them in a small casserole dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the meat balls.
Cook 45 minutes at 375°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cranberry-orange-pear relish
directions: Quarter oranges and discard center pith and seeds.
Quarter pear and discard center core and seeds.
Pick over cranberries; rinse.
Put oranges, pear and cranberries through a food chopper. Add sugar and mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Ready for griddle.

title: cherry gelatine bars
directions: Mix the first three ingredients; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Prick with a fork and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Chop green peppers and onion.
Cook in oil in 5-quart pan until tender.
Cut zucchini and squash into fourths lengthwise, then into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add zucchini, squash, chili powder, sugar, salt and ground red pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, beans and corn (with liquid).
Cook over high until boiling. Reduce to medium-low.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi(easy recipe!)
directions: *By the potato section in supermarket.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, milk and cinnamon.
Melt margarine in a pan in the oven.
Take the pan out and put the dough in.
Then drain the peaches.
Put them in the pan.
Then put them in an oven at 350°.

title: cheese torte
directions: Mix all together and shape into a mold. Chill overnight. Top with jam. Makes large mold. May divide and make 2 smaller molds. Serve with crackers or Fritos.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In mixing bowl, cream oleo and sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough into balls, using rounded teaspoon of dough for each.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll balls of dough in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: homemade eagle brand
directions: Blend once, scrape down sides.
Then blend until completely smooth.
Pour into container; let stand until cool and thickened. Use, refrigerate or freeze, covered.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: mexican chicken bake
directions: Cube chicken.
Butter shallow casserole dish.
Mix soup, onions, milk and chilies.
Place half the Doritos in the bottom. Next place half the chicken.
Cover with half the soup and milk; repeat 3 layers again.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: avocado cream
directions: Place chicken stock, avocados and lime juice in a blender or food processor.
Whirl until smooth.
(This is easiest done in two batches.)
Add salt and pepper to taste and chill, covered, in the refrigerator for an hour or more.
Serve in chilled soup plates garnished with chives or parsley.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake according to package directions.
Spread one-half of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
In saucepan, melt caramels at medium heat with sweetened condensed milk.
Watch carefully so it doesn't burn.
Spread evenly on baked cake.
Cover caramel topping with rest of cake batter.
Bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes.
When cool, frost with whipped topping.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: miniature pizzas
directions: Mix soup, garlic and oregano.
With small spoon dip mixture onto crackers and sprinkle with Cheddar and Parmesan cheese.
Place crackers on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes. Watch!
May brown quickly.

title: pearl's pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white to peaks.
Gradually add brown sugar and vanilla.
Fold in pecan halves.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet, making sure there is a pecan half in each one.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn off heat and leave in oven 30 minutes longer.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and applesauce.
Beat until smooth.
Turn into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's sweet potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Put in a casserole dish.

title: yams and pineapple
directions: Peel, boil and mash yams.
Heat pineapple and honey together just until warm.
Add pineapple and honey to mashed yams.
Add butter.
Put in serving dish and top with nutmeg.

title: monkey cake
directions: Combine 1 cup of sugar with cinnamon in a bag.
Cut each biscuit in quarters.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture and line a greased tube pan.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening in large mixer bowl until light. Add sugar and brown sugar gradually; beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with evaporated milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Spread glaze over cake.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: chocolate nog punch
directions: Combine softened ice cream, eggnog and chocolate syrup; mix well.
Pour into punch bowl or pitcher.
Add club soda gradually, stirring gently.
Float whipped cream on surface of punch, if desired, or spoon onto each glass; garnish with shaved chocolate. Makes about 11 cups or 20 to 22 half cups.

title: big al's taters
directions: Fry bacon crisp; set to side.
Save bacon grease.
Cover potatoes with water.
Add bacon grease and onion.
Cook until firm but tender.
Dice bacon.
Mix cheese, milk, sour cream and bacon. Drain potatoes.
Layer in casserole dish.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: italian sausage and peppers
directions: Brown sausage in skillet. In another skillet, add a little oil and saute garlic and the peppers (cut into strips). Season the peppers with salt. Drain sausage and combine with peppers. Add the sauteed onion.

title: percolator punch
directions: Combine juices in a percolator.
Place sugar and spices in basket and perk.

title: greek salad
directions: Stir together and serve cold.

title: lasagna style bow tie dish
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. Partially cook pasta 1/2 time required on package.
In skillet, heat oil.
Saute onion 1 minute.
Stir in ground meat.
Cook until browned.
Add spaghetti sauce and bring to boil.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onions until brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread beef mixture in pie plate; sprinkle with cheese. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over meat and cheese in pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: frozen banana split salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze.
Cut into squares and serve on a crisp bed of lettuce!

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Set aside.
Combine tomato juice, vegetable oil, chili beans, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add hamburger and onion.
Let simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef paprika
directions: Brown beef in pork drippings.
Add onions and chopped garlic and cook until transparent.
Sprinkle in flour and stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook gently 1 1/2 to 2 hours (or longer in crock-pot).

title: cheese and strawberries
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a ring.
Put strawberry preserves in a dish on the middle.
Serve with crackers.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onions, celery and garlic in hot oil until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer uncovered 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 2 teaspoons of water. Stir into sauce.
Cook and add shrimp and peppers.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: dixie dogs(corn dogs)
directions: Cover wieners with mixture and deep fry until done.

title: virginia's mexican casserole
directions: Line a 10 x 14-inch baking pan with 6 tortillas.
Add beef which has been browned with onions and seasoned with chili powder. Spread over beef mixture the cans of beans with juice.
Place sliced cheese over this; cover with remaining 6 tortillas.
Cover tortillas with mixture of soup and tomatoes.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: sourdough brownies
directions: Mix
together
the
starter, flour and dry milk.
Cover bowl with
plastic
wrap;
set in warm place for 2 to 3 hours until
it smells
yeasty.
Melt
together
the shortening and chocolate over low heat or in microwave.
Add sugar, vanilla, salt
and soda;
beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well
after each.
Add nuts.
Combine with sourdough mixture; beat
well. Pour
into	greased
and floured 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Bake
for
to
40 minutes (until toothpick inserted
in center comes out clean).
If desired, frost with prepared chocolate frosting.

title: sizzling sausage stir-fry
directions: Cook rice and keep warm.
Saute vegetables in oil until crisp and tender.
Add sausage and season to taste.
Heat thoroughly. Mix in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and serve over warm rice, sprinkling with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix all together. Pour into greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes. Good served with Chicken Enchilada.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls out onto a long cookie sheet.
Bake as directed on package; let cool.
Mix dressing mix, salad dressing and cream cheese together and spread on cooled rolls.
Cover cream cheese mixture with vegetables and sprinkle with cheese. Refrigerate until you want to eat.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, oleo, syrup and cream of tartar for 7 minutes. Place popcorn in large roaster; pour sugar mixture over top, stirring, until coated.
Place in oven and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
You can also add 2 cups salted peanuts to popcorn before baking.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly bits
directions: Make dough stiff.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
You may add coconut, nuts or chocolate chips.

title: ri's chocolate pecan pie
directions: Prepare crust per directions.
In medium bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, chocolate, margarine and vanilla until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with hands.
Press and mold into a long, smooth roll about 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper; chill until stiff.
With a thin, sharp knife, cut in thin slices 1/16 to 1/8-inch thick.
Place slices a little apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes. Yields 6 dozen.

title: scandinavian salad or bean salad
directions: Mix.
Add
salt to taste.
Use just part of the liquids in the
vegetables.
Mix
well and pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.	Drain.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower until fork tender.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and cheese.
Heat 2 minutes on full power in microwave.
Pour over cauliflower and serve hot.

title: polish wedding pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, 1 cup at a time and cream after each.
Add flour mixed with salt, alternating with milk and flavoring, ending with flour.
Add cherries and nuts.
Pour into greased angel food pan.
Place in cold oven on lower shelf.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours.
Let stand in pan 1/2 hour before moving from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix everything together; spread 2/3 of mixture in 8 x 8-inch pan, patting well on sides and bottom.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Crust:
Cut Crisco into flour; add cold water and vinegar. Divide in half and roll out; cut into fourths.
Peel and slice apple onto each piece; sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top.
Add pat of butter.
Fold up and pinch together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a pan (or bowl for microwave) melt together next 4 ingredients and pour over top.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili dish
directions: Brown meat with the next 4 ingredients and drain.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Beginning with Fritos on bottom and meat mixture next, add any toppings you want to (cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, green olives, ripe olives, salsa sauce and onion).
(You may already have this one, but it is really good and not much trouble.)

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Poke holes in cake and pour Kahlua over it.
Cut cake into 1 inch squares.
Prepare mousse. Arrange cake squares in bottom of deep glass dish.
Cover with mousse, then Cool Whip and candy.
Repeat layers until dish is filled.

title: italian chicken pockets
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
In skillet, heat oil and brown chicken.
Stir in spaghetti seasoning, bell pepper, water and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 to 3 minutes until thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Cut each pita bread in half.
Fill pockets with chicken mixture and top with grated cheese.

title: salad of gold
directions: Put gelatin and hot water into blender container.
Cover and process and stir until dissolved.
Remove feeder cap and add syrup, vinegar and milk.
Push liquify and add cream cheese.
When mixture is smooth, stop blender.
Add carrot pieces and pineapple. Replace cover and process 1 cycle at grind.
Pour into a 2-quart ring mold and chill until set.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and 6 tablespoons butter; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tatonka vegetable soup
directions: Saute diced onions, sliced leeks, diced celery, carrots and diced mixed peppers in oil until onions become transparent.
Add ground buffalo.
Saute until lightly browned.
Blend in flour. Blend in minced garlic, chicken and beef bases and tomato paste. Add water.
Heat, stirring continuously, until thickened.
Add black pepper, thyme, marjoram and bay leaf.
Add potatoes and tomato puree.
Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 45 minutes.
Add diced tomatoes, green beans and corn. Simmer until green beans are tender, about 10 minutes.
Blend in fresh minced parsley.

title: summer punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, prepared with ice ring, add one container of sherbet.
Pour in 1 1/2 quarts ginger ale.
When sherbet softens, add remaining half gallon of sherbet and 1 1/2 quarts of ginger ale.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Marinate chicken 2 hours with soy sauce, sugar, sake and ginger juice.
Fry in oil until moisture is gone.
Lay on top of shredded cabbage.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Pound seasoned flour into both sides of round steak. Cook onions in Wesson oil until tender; remove and set aside. Brown meat in oil; drain fat.
Top meat with onions and tomatoes. Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender. Thicken sauce, if desired, and season to taste.
Serve with potatoes, rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco tossed salad
directions: Cook and stir ground beef over medium heat until light brown; drain.
Stir in taco sauce mix.
Toss lettuce, tomato, cheese and chips.
Spoon hot beef mixture and salad dressing over lettuce mixture.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cookie apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine apples, brown sugar, flour, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and lemon juice. Toss and coat apples well. Spoon into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Using 1/2 of the cookie dough, drop by teaspoon evenly over the apples.
In a small bowl, combine sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over cookie dough.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until top is golden brown and apples are tender.

title: egg pudding
directions: Cream cheese; add sugar.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Pour into greased bowl.
Set into pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole pie
directions: Mix chicken, broth, soup, vegetables, onion, salt and pepper. Spread mixture in casserole dish.
Top with crust.

title: borscht(yield: 6 servings)
directions: Lightly spray a 4 to 6-quart slow cooker with vegetable oil cooking spray. Place the remaining ingredients in the slow cooker and stir to combine. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or until vegetables are tender. Add salt to taste. If desired, serve with dollops of sour cream and fresh dill.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Chill before serving.
Very good with fresh strawberries, pineapple, peaches, pears and bananas.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and ketchup well.
Place chicken wings in a casserole; pour mixture over wings.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream shortening.
Add other ingredients; beat until desired consistency.
For stiffer icing, add more powdered sugar.
For thinner, add more water.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain pineapple and mix with beans.
Add ketchup and brown sugar to taste; mix well.
Pour into baking dish and spread bacon slices over top.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until bacon is done.

title: cheesecake(individual servings)
directions: Mix thoroughly with electric mixer. Line muffin pan with bake cups. Place 1 vanilla wafer in each cup. Spoon
mixture

into cups. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes. Cool and top with favorite cheese cake topping. Can be frozen - thaws quickly. If freezing, do not add topping until ready to serve. Great for showers, receptions, and parties.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling; stir in jello until dissolved.
Let cool, then add buttermilk; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until set.
This is good with other flavors of jello too; just pick your favorite!

title: red velvet mocha frosting
directions: Cream butter until light.
Sift in confectioners sugar, beating constantly, until fluffy.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl; mix well.
Add to creamed mixture and beat until of spreading consistency, adding additional coffee, if necessary.

title: funnel cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture; beat smooth with rotary beater.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease pan well before pouring mixture.
Mix creamed corn, milk and eggs. Add self-rising corn meal, jalapeno and green peppers, onion and 1/2 cup of cheese. Mix well. Pour into pan or casserole dish and bake at 400°
until golden brown. Sprinkle with remaining cheese on top and return to oven until cheese has melted.
Cut into squares. Serve hot.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add other ingredients. Mix well. Cook until thick. Add vegetables. Put in casserole pan and top with mashed potatoes. Spread with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banapple
directions: Mix well for quick dessert.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook at low heat the beef.
(Simmer on top of stove.) Cool beef and cut into small pieces.
Strain broth and add to soup. While meat is cooking, start the rest of soup.
Add onion soup mix to 1 quart water, stir and add the rest of the vegetables.
Add beef and strained broth.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add additional water as needed.
This soup is best made a day ahead and reheated day of serving.

title: crabmeat loaf
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients above together.
Chill overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch, or 3 smaller loaf pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch.

title: *devil's food cake
directions: Combine cocoa, soda and boiling water in small bowl; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and beat. Add cocoa mixture and beat.
Combine milk and vinegar.
Sift salt with flour.
Add alternately to batter.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 2 (8-inch) layers or 9 x 15-inch loaf.

title: bivin's baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 3 hours in crock-pot.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Combine soup mix, soups, sour cream, milk, sherry and mushrooms.
Add two thirds of this mix to the 2 uncooked rices in a bowl and mix well.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Place chicken breasts on rice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour remaining one third of soup mix over the top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350 covered for 11/4 hours.
Remove cover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Then add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and whipping cream alternately, begin and end with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake in preheated oven 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: clinch mountain vinegar pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, vinegar, flour and water in double boiler and cook until thick and smooth, stirring occasionally.
Just before removing from heat, stir in butter and lemon extract. Pour into baked pie shell.
If desired, the pie may be topped with frosting or whipped cream.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with marshmallow creme.
Serve with fresh fruit Especially good with apple slices, bananas, strawberries.

title: golden carrot bake(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In saucepan, combine carrots, water, rice and salt.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 25 minutes.
Do not drain!
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the shredded cheese, milk, eggs, onion and pepper.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven about 1 hour.
Top with remaining cheese and return to oven about 2 minutes to melt the cheese.
